</HEAD>
<BODY>
<CENTER><H3>KLAUS von KLITZING</H3></CENTER>
Born 28th June 1943 in Schroda (Poser), German nationality. <BR>
<BR>
February 1962:
<UL>Abitur in Quakenbruck</UL><BR><BR>

April 1962 to March 1969:
<UL>Technical University Braunschweig Diploma in Physics.<BR>
Title of diploma work: &quot;Lifetime Measurements on InSb&quot; (Prof.
F. R. Kessler)</UL><BR><BR>

May 1969 to Nov. 1980:
<UL>University W&uuml;rzburg (Prof. Dr. G. Landwehr)<BR>
Thesis work about: &quot;Galvanomagnetic Properties of Tellurium in Strong<BR>
Magnetic Fields&quot; (Ph.D. in 1972).<BR>
Habilitation in 1978.<BR>
The most important publication related to the Nobel Prize appeared in:<BR>
Phys. Rev. Letters <I>45</I>, 494 (1980).<BR>
Research work at the Clarendon Laboratory, Oxford (1975 to 1976) and<BR>
High Magnetic Field Laboratory, Grenoble (1979 to 1980)</UL><BR><BR>

Nov. 1980 to Dec. 1984:
<UL>Professor at the Technical University, M&uuml;nchen</UL><BR>
<BR>
Since January 1985:
<UL> Director at the Max-Planck-Institut fur Festkorperforschung,
Stuttgart.</UL>
