<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Activities at Nobel Forum</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<HR>
<H1>Activities at Nobel Forum</H1>
<BR>
<HR>The Nobel Forum is used for scientific meetings, lectures and seminars
organized by the Medical Nobel Assembly or the Karolinska
Institute. The activities include the Karolinska
Research Lectures, a regular seminar series given by prominent, invited
scientists and teachers at the Karolinska Institute and other academic institutions.
A press conference is organized when the Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
is announced in October. In December the Laureates are presented to the
press.<BR>
&#180;<BR>
<HR><BR>
<P><CENTER><B>KAROLINSKA RESEARCH LECTURES AT NOBEL FORUM AUTUMN 1996, 4 
PM</B></CENTER> <P>Thursday, Sept 19: <BR>
Professor <B>Martin Raff</B>, MRC Laboratory for Molecular Cell Biology,
University College, London, UK<BR>
Title: <I>Size Control: the Regulation of Cell Numbers in Animal Development
</I><BR>
Host: Professor Bj&ouml;rn Vennstr&ouml;m <BR>
<BR>
Thursday, Oct 3: <BR>
Professor <B>Kathryn B. Horwitz</B>, Department of Medicine, University
of Colorado Health Sciences Center, Denver, Colorado, USA <BR>
Title: <I>Molecular Mechanisms of Steroid Antagonist Action and Hormone
Resistance in Breast Cancer </I><BR>
Host: Professor Jan-Ake Gustafsson <BR>
<BR>
Thursday, Oct 17: <BR>
Professor <B>Sydney Brenner</B>, King's College, Cambridge, UK <BR>
Title: <I>The Pufferfish Genome: a Reference Vertebrate Genome </I><BR>
Host: Professor Georg Klein <BR>
<BR>
Thursday, Oct 31: <BR>
Professor <B>Stanley B. Prusiner</B>, Department of Neurology, UCSF, San
Francisco, California, USA <BR>
Title: <I>Prion Biology and Diseases - The Mad Cow Crisis</I><BR>
Host: Professor Erling Norrby <BR>
