<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME: Who We Are</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Who We Are</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<CENTER><H3>The Society for Mining, Metallurgy, and Exploration, Inc. advances the worldwide mining and minerals community through information exchange and professional development.</H3></CENTER>

<UL TYPE=square>

<LI>SME exists to provide timely, quality technical information to its members on a global level.

<LI>SME is the forum for leaders of international mining and minerals organizations to share and disseminate knowledge and information.

<LI>SME is active in providing the public with an understanding of what mining and minerals mean for day-to-day life.  

</UL>

<P>SME focuses on increasing the knowledge and skills of mineral professionals.  With more than 16,000 members in 25 countries, the society continues to evolve in response to the changing needs of its members around the world.</P>

<P>SME is the technical organization for professionals in the mineral industry. It addresses their needs through its four <A HREF="benefits.stml"><STRONG>divisions:</STRONG></A> Coal, Industrial Minerals, Mining & Exploration and Mineral & Metallurgical Processing; the Minerals Resource Management Committee and the newly-created Environmental Division. SME members have the technical expertise, acquired through training and experience, to pioneer innovations and to make the decisions that generate growth in an industry facing increasing challenges.</P>

<P>Through the benefits of publications, meetings, education and GEM programs, SME is the minerals industry resource for the successful minerals professional. </P>

<P><B><A HREF="members.stml">SME membership</A></B> benefits include; group health and life insurance program, affinity credit card program, discounted car rental, job bank and home mortgage relocation program. SME publishes the prestigious periodicals <B><A HREF="me.stml"><I>Mining Engineering</I></A></B> and <B><A HREF="mmpj.stml"><I>Minerals and Metallurgical Processing</I></A></B> and timely <B><A HREF="books/booklist.stml">books</A></B> and proceedings. <B><A HREF="meetings.stml">SME meetings</A></B> include; the <B><A HREF="annmtg.stml">SME Annual Meeting and Exhibit</A></B>, topical conferences, specialty symposia and short courses.  <B>SME is actively involved in education</B>. It is a member of the Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology and sponsors an active student chapter program. <B>SME GEM (Government, Education and Mining)</B> distributes free minerals education materials to school teachers, develops new educational products, including computer programs, videos, posters and brochures, and has an established video lending library to assist educational programs.

<CENTER><H3>SME<BR>The Minerals Community at Work</H3></CENTER>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>sme.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
817.</P>

