<IMG SRC="art/newlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12>

SME on the Internet</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>What's New</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<H1><HR><A HREF="apcom/index.html">APCOM</A>: Application of Computers and Operations Research in the Mineral Industry</H1>
<P>
Information about upcoming and past APCOM proceedings
</P>

<CENTER>
<A NAME="minesim"><H1><A HREF="http://www.uidaho.edu/mining_school">Minesim '96</A></H1></A>
<P>1st International Symposium on Mine Simulation via the Internet-Dec. 2-13, 1996</P>
</CENTER>
<P>This pioneering Internet symposium is organized by the Dept. of Mining and Metallurgy of the University of Idaho and the Department of Mining Engineering and Metallurgy of the National Technical University of Athens, Greece (NTUA). The event is cosponsored by <B><A HREF="index.html">SME</A></B>.</P>
<P>Major topics of the symposium include mine system simulation, artificial intelligence, expert systems, virtual reality, neural networks and robotics. The symposium attempts to merge historical developments of these topics with current mining applications.</P>
<P><B>Minesim '96</B> papers will be published on a Web site developed and maintained by NTUA. The site's URL is <A HREF="http://www.metal.ntua.gr/msslab">http://www.metal.ntua.gr/msslab</A>. Over the symposium's duration, Internet participants can read and download papers, make queries and offer comments and criticism.</P>
<P>Paper abstracts may be submitted until June 1, 1996. The abstracts, written in English and confined to 300-500 words, should be e-mailed to <B>both</B> symposium chairmen: John R. Sturgul (<B><A HREF="mailto:sturgul@uidaho.edu">sturgul@uidaho.edu</A></B>) and George N. Panagiotou (<B><A HREF="mailto:panagiotou@metal.ntua.gr">panagiotou@metal.ntua.gr</A></B>). Abstracts should include paper title, author name(s), e-mail address and affiliation.</P>

<P><HR>Aid for purchasers of minerals-industry products and services will also be posted in a <A HREF="meads.stml"><STRONG><CITE>Mining Engineering</CITE> Advertiser Profiles</STRONG></A> page. It will profile some of the companies that advertise their products or services in SME's <I>Mining Engineering.</I>

<P><HR>SME will post its new programs, event calendar and other inaugurated services on this page. The society is undertaking a major electronic publishing, digital communication program that will make technical and newsworthy information more readily and/or quickly available through Internet resources, CD-ROM media, E-mail interactivity and other electronic forms to further SME's primary goal of providing information to its members and others in the worldwide minerals industry.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Customer Service</STRONG>.

