<A HREF="prospectus.stml"><H2>1997 SME Annual Meeting Exhibitor Prospectus</H2></A>
<CENTER>
<H2><FONT SIZE=5>THE SME EXHIBIT</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE=3>Defines Your Exposure to the Mining Industry</FONT></H2>
</CENTER>
<P>The international minerals industry is changing rapidly. SME members are affected by rising costs and increasing environmental demands. They pursue knowledge and technology that will keep them competitive and aggressive in a challenging environment. To get ahead, minerals professionals look to the SME Annual Meeting and Exhibit for the technical expertise to pioneer innovations and make the decisions that generate growth. SME attendees seek partnerships with companies that can provide tools and vision for the future.</P>
<P>The 1997 SME Annual Meeting and Exhibit brings the entire minerals industry together under one roof, at one time. By exhibiting with SME, you showcase your product or service to more than 5,000 qualified industry experts. Their business agenda is actively at work on the exhibit floor. 65% of SME members make purchasing decisions for their company. In short, the SME Exhibit attracts the people you need to see.</P>

<A HREF="techprog.stml"><H2>1997 SME Annual Meeting Technical Program</H2></A>

<P>For more details refer to the insert in the November issue of <I>MINING ENGINEERING</I>, or to recieve a copy of the complete announcement, contact:</P>
<P>Meetings Department, SME<BR>
PO Box 625002<BR>
Littleton CO 80162-5002</P>
<P>800-673-3132 or 303-973-9550</P>
<P>Fax: 303-979-3461</P>
<P>e mail: <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A>.</P>

<H2>Specialty Programming</H2>
<H3>Comminution Practices</H3>
<P>(six sessions)</P>

<P><STRONG>Industrial Case Studies<BR>
Mill Drives<BR>
High Pressure Rolls<BR>
Circuit Design and Maintenance<BR>
Ultrafine Grinding, New Devices, and Recycling<BR>
Instrumentation and Control</P></STRONG>

<P><I>S. Komar Kawatra</I>, Michigan Technological University Metallurgical and Materials Engineering Dept., 1400 Townsend Dr., Houghton, MI 49931-1200, (906-487-2064).</P>



