<HEAD>

<TITLE>Membership: Benefits of SME Membership</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<IMG SRC="art/memlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12>

Membership:</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Benefits of SME Membership</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>Professional development is not achieved independently. Change - and the pace of new information, technology and global competition is staggering. Join with other minerals professionals in addressing your professional needs. SME is - mining engineers, geologists, scientists, chemical engineers, environmental specialists, regulators, educators, technicians, marketers, suppliers and managers. This global network facilitates the transfer of innovation and skill in the most time-effective manner possible.

<P>Founded in 1872, SME is the home for today's minerals professional. SME members are a reservoir of experience and know-how available to professionals around the world. Via SME <A HREF="publications.stml">publications</A>, <A HREF="annmtg.stml">meetings</A>, the <A HREF="me.stml"><I>Mining Engineering</I></A> magazine, and 73 <A HREF="sections.stml">local sections</A>, you can network with other professionals plus acquaint yourself with new technologies, business concepts, industry direction and opportunities. Attempting to acquire this broad base of knowledge independently would be virtually impossible - and all for one low annual membership price!

<P>SME membership also provides you with the opportunity to give back to your profession by serving on a committee, being active at the local section level, presenting a paper at a meeting, or educating the public about the importance of minerals in our everyday lives.

<H3>Divisions</H3>

<P>SME members are affiliated with a division in the society. The technical programming offered at each annual meeting is accomplished through the division structure. An incoming member states which division would be his/her main interest; i.e., Coal Division, Mining & Exploration Division, Industrial Minerals Division, Mineral & Metallurgical Processing Division.

<P>Coal Division - The objective of the Coal Division shall be to provide a medium of cooperation among those interested in any way in coal, and to promote the use of coal as a major source of energy by creating interest in coal as a profession, and to advance the technologies in exploration, mining, and utilization through meetings, programs, publications, and encouraging continuing education. The Coal Division meets each year at the annual meeting to conduct business, confer awards and scholarships, and through division representatives on the executive committee and the board of directors perpetuates the business of the SME

<P>The Division's Unit Committees are: Coal Availability/Recoverability; Environmental; Health and Safety; Preparation; Research and Development; Surface Mining; Underground Mining; Underground Ventilation (joint with M&E); and Utilization.

<P>The present Coal Division Chairman is Danrick W. Alexander, Consol Inc., Consol Plaza, 1800 Washington Rd., Pittsburgh, PA 15241-1421, phone 412-831-4629, fax 412-831-4916.

<P><B>Mining & Exploration Division</B> - The objective of the Mining & Exploration Division shall be to furnish a medium of cooperation between and among those directly engaged in metal mining, research, and specialized aspects of mining, and those engaged in the technologies of exploration. To further the objective toward a common goal and advance these branches of the mining industry, the division will promote published papers, arrange meetings and programs, and encourage education on any subject related to these phases of the industry. The M&E Division meets each year at the annual meeting to conduct business, confer awards and scholarships, and through division representatives on the executive committee and the board of directors perpetuates the business of the SME.

<P>The Division's Unit Committees are: Environmental Control and Reclamation; Geochemistry; Geology; Geomechanics; Geophysics; Hydrology; Mechanical Mining and Excavation; Open Pit Mining; Operations Research; Solution Mining; Underground Mining; and Underground Ventilation (joint with Coal).

<P>The present M&E Division Chairman is Michael Karmis, Virginia Polytechnic Institute and State University, 100 Holden Hall, Mining and Mineral Engineering, Blacksburg, VA 24061-0239, phone 703-231-6671, fax 703-231-4070.

<P><B>Industrial Minerals Division</B> - The purpose of the Industrial Minerals Division shall be to further the arts and sciences involved in the exploration for and production and use of industrial minerals; to hold meetings which provide for the gathering of the profession and the presentation and discussion of professional papers; to obtain and promote publication of such professional papers; to promote the exchange of information and ideas in areas of mutual interest with other divisions and societies; and to promote student interest in industrial minerals. The division meets each year at the annual meeting to conduct business.

<P>The Division's Technical Committees are: Agricultural Materials; Ceramics and Refractories; Chemical Raw Materials; Clays; Construction Materials; Environmental and Reclamation Issues; Filler, Filter Aids and Absorbents; Marketing, Economics and Transportation; and Specialty Minerals.

<P>The present Industrial Minerals Division Chairman is Nikhil C. Trivedi, Specialty Minerals Inc., 9 Highland Ave., Bethlehem, PA 18017-9482, phone 610-861-3405, fax 610-861-3408.

<P><B>Mineral & Metallurgical Processing Division</B> - The objectives of the Mineral & Metallurgical Processing Division shall be to furnish a medium of cooperation among those interested in the basic unit processes and unit operations of mineral and metallurgical processing; to promote the advancement of mineral and metallurgical technology through meetings for professional intercourse; and to stimulate the preparation, reading, discussion and circulation of papers therewith. This division, too, meets each year at the annual meeting to conduct business, confer awards, nominate committee members, and perpetuate the business of the society.

<P>The Division's Technical Committees are: Concentration; Crushing and Grinding; Hydrometallurgical Processing; Metallurgical Processing Fundamentals; Mineral Processing Fundamentals; Plant Design and Practice; Process Control and Computer Applications; Process Mineralogy; and Pyrometallurgical Processing.

<P>The present MPD Chairman is Arthur A. Schweizer, Glenbrook Nickel Co., Cominco American Resources, PO Box 85, Riddle, OR 97469, phone 503-874-3171, fax 503-874-3380.

<P><B>Minerals Resource Management Committee</B> - Rather than a division, this is a standing committee serving the society through representatives from the above named divisions concerning mineral economics and minerals resource management. Programming is provided for each annual meeting, as well as technical review for articles submitted for publication in this area.

<P>The Minerals Resource Management Committee Chairman is L. Pat Gochnour, Gochnour & Associates, PO Box 3207, Englewood, CO 80155, phone 303-770-7480, fax 303-721-9298.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

