<HEAD>

<TITLE>Membership: How to Join or Change Your Membership</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml>
<IMG SRC="art/memlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>How to Join or Change Your Membership</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<H3>How to Become a Student Member</H3>

Those studying in the minerals fields can enhance their career opportunities by joining SME before they begin their careers. Information on the <A HREF="benefits_student.stml">benefits of SME student membership</A> is available.

<H4>Qualifications:</H4>

<P>A student in good standing at a minerals school who has been sponsored by an instructor (preferably an SME member) may join SME as a Student Member.

<H4>Dues: </H4>

<P>Dues are established by the SME Board of Directors, and are currently only $15.00 per year. The dues payment must be submitted with the membership application.

<H4>Advantages:</H4>

<P>Students may purchase books and register for SME meetings at a student discount - a considerable savings over the membership price.

<H4>Membership Application:</H4>

<P>To apply for Student Membership, contact Member Services today and request an application. Phone 800-763-3132, or 303-973-9550, fax 303-0973-3845, e-mail <A HREF="mailto:smeaime@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A>. An <A HREF="application.stml">online copy of the membership application</A> is available as well.

<H3>How to Become an SME Member</H3>

Members are accepted through a written application process. Please call Member Services and request a membership application, phone 800-763-3132, or 303-973-9550, fax 303-973-3845, e-mail <A HREF="mailto:smeaime@aol.com">smeaime@aol.com</A>.

<H4>Qualifications</H4>

<P><B>Full Member:</B> Employed a minimum of five years in the following areas relevant to minerals exploration, extraction, production, processing, economics and metallurgy: educator; engineering; scientific; related earth science; management; or technical sales of equipment and supplies used in minerals activities. Three years of this experience must be in a position of responsibility. Education in lieu of professional experience requirements will be given as follows: Baccalaureate degree in engineering, mineral economics or related earth and environmental sciences equals two years; Masters degree in any of the above disciplines equals three years; Doctoral degree equals four years. Highest degree earned is considered, not cumulative.

<P><B>Associate Member:</B> Employed or educated in the following areas relevant to minerals exploration, extraction, production, processing economics and metallurgy: educator; engineering; scientific; related earth science; management; or technical sales of equipment and supplies used in minerals activities. Those who eventually qualify for Member status must request a change of status to Member grade, which is subject to review.

<H4>Fill Out the Application</H4>

<P>The application asks for information about the prospective member: name, address, employer, phone number, fax number, birth date, etc. The qualifications required for each member grade are also listed on the application. The endorsement of a current SME member is required on each new application. This requirement was established by the Board of Directors to ensure that applicants who applied enhanced the professionalism of the society. 

<P>Information regarding level of education, areas of interest, business and industry association, and record of experience are required. The applicant must sign and date the application. 

<P>Additional journals may be requested, in addition to the <A HREF="me.stml">Mining Engineering</A> journal, that is mailed monthly to SME members. 

<P>Provision for payment by credit card is included on the application.

<H4>How Long Does It Take?</H4>

<P>Once the application is received in the SME headquarters, approval takes approximately 10 days. Applications are reviewed for membership qualifications. Not filling out the application completely results in delay of approval for membership.

<H3>Notification of Approval</H3>

<P>Applicants are notified in writing once the application has been approved. They are notified of their SME membership number, or their account standing, and additional benefits available to SME members.

<H3>Dues and Entrance Fee</H3>

<P>Dues are US$80.00 for Associate Members and Members. Dues are billed on a calendar year basis. A full year's dues, plus the $20.00 entrance fee, are required on submission of a new member application. New member dues are prorated throughout the year based on entrance date into the society. Any overage collected for a full year's dues will be credited to the next calendar year.

<P>Entrance Fee - A one-time $20.00 entrance fee is assessed on application for admission into SME. All or part of this entrance fee is rebated back to local sections to help in individual programming and education.

<DT><H3>Membership Questions</H3>

<DT><B>Can you pay your dues by credit card?</B>

<DD>Yes, you may pay by credit card by downloading the credit card information from this file, completing and faxing to us at 303-973-3845.

<DT><B>Do you have questions regarding again becoming an active member in the society?</B>

<DD>If you have not paid SME dues for three years or more, it will be necessary to fill out an application for reinstatement as your name is no longer included on the membership rolls.  Call 800-763-3121, or 303-973-9550,  and request a reinstatement form from Member Services.

<P>If you have not paid this or the previous year's dues, all you need do to return to active status is pay the current dues.  You can pay by credit card if you wish by downloading the credit card information from this file, completing the form, and faxing to us at 303-973-3845, or by calling headquarters at 800-763-3121 and paying by credit card over the phone.</P>

<DT><B>Do you have questions regarding Full Membership in the society?</B>

<DD>Those Associate Members who have been employed in the minerals industry for more than 5 years may apply to Full Member grade.  There is no automatic upgrade to Full Member, but must be requested.  Please contact the Membership Coordinator at this e-mail address, or call the 800 number, to begin the upgrade-to-Full-Member process.

</DL>

<P>Local Sections - The board of directors authorized a one year 25% dues discount for those sections interested in a membership development campaign. The sections must contact headquarters, Member Services, to receive the necessary forms for this offer. In addition to the 25% dues offer, the sections can choose to waive the entrance fee, and provide the new applicant with even further savings.

<H3>Membership Application</H3>

<P>Contact General Members Services today and request an application. Phone 800-763-3132, or 303-973-9550, fax 303-0973-3845, e-mail <A HREF="mailto:smeaime@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A>. An <A HREF="application.stml">online copy of the membership application</A> is available as well.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Customer Service</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>joinchange.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
842.</P>

</BODY>

