<DL>

<DT><H3>Careers in Engineering</H3>

<DD>Will you become a member of our great industry by pursuing a career as a minerals engineer?  Explore the possibilities in the exciting fields of geological, mining, environmental, mineral processing or metallurgical engineering!  Whether you're considering a career in the minerals industry, are already enrolled in a minerals-related program, or have already embarked on your career path, the information available here can help!

<DT><H3>Careers</H3>

<DD>

<P><UL>

<LI><B><A HREF="career-matls.stml">Career Materials</A></B><BR>

Career information and publications may be ordered directly from SME.  Contact us at <B><A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A></B>.

<UL>

<LI>Careers for Engineers in the Minerals Industry

<LI>Guide to Minerals Schools

<LI>Career Planning Workshop booklets

</UL>

<DT><H3><B><A HREF="career_wkshp.stml">Career Planning Workshop</A></B></H3>

<DD>The 1997 Career Planning Workshop promises to be valuable networking and information-gathering opportunity for students or anyone interested in advancing their career.  Planning is underway.  Send your ideas and comments to <B><A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A></B>.

</DL>

