<HEAD>

<TITLE>Membership: SME Scholarships</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml>
<IMG SRC="art/memlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>SME Scholarships</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<P>The Society for Mining, Metallurgy, and Exploration, Inc. is a membership organization devoted to the pursuit of educational, scientific and charitable activities as they affect minerals industry professionals.

<P>The education programs of the society are vigorous and ongoing. For the professionals already in the minerals industry, the society provides a well-balanced continuing education program featuring short courses and workshops.

<P>Each year the society provides the following scholarships for the SME Student Member who is presently enrolled, and has completed his/her sophmore year in a college/university, and majoring in a field within the minerals industry. Requests for scholarships will be taken after enrollment in fall classes (August through October).

<OL>
<LI><B>Coal Division Scholarship</B> - offered to students majoring in mining or mineral engineering degree-granting programs that are ABET accredited and who are engaged in coal-related activities.

<LI><B>Gerald V. Henderson Industrial Minerals Memorial Scholarship</B> - student must be enrolled in a regular course of study leading to a degree in geology, minerals engineering, mining engineering or mineral economics.

<LI><B>Pfleider Memorial Scholarship</B> - offered to student with a major in mining engineering.

<LI><B>Mining & Exploration Division Scholarship</B> - applicant must currently be enrolled in an ABET-accredited mineral-related program and majoring in mining, geology, or other field of specialization covered by the Mining & Exploration Division's technical unit committees.

<LI><B>Mineral & Metallurgical Processing Division Scholarship</B> - student must be enrolled in a department that grants a degree in metallurgy or metallurgical engineering and must have expressed an interest in pursuing a career in the area of mineral processing.
</OL>

<P>For more details and scholarship applications please contact - Society for Mining, Metallurgy, and Exploration, Member Services, PO Box 625002, Littleton, CO 80126-5002 303-973-9550, e-mail <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A>.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

