<HEAD>

<TITLE>Careers: Professional Registration</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<IMG SRC="art/careers.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 BORDER=0>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Professional Registration</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<H2>SME Professional Registration</H2>

<P>The SME Professional Registration Committee prepares problems for the Mining/Mineral Engineering examination for registration as a professional engineer. The committee sends these problems and their solutions to the National Council of Examiners for Engineering and Surveying (NCEES) for formatting and printing. After a final review by the SME Professional Registration Committee, NCEES distributes the exam to the various states.</P>

<P>After administering the exams, the states return them to NCEES. NCEES then distributes the exams for grading to the technical group or society that prepared the exam. After grading, the exams are returned to NCEES, which then returns them to the appropriate state boards. The mining/mineral exam scores are computer-analyzed each year by a committee member.</P>

<P>Examinees may request (for a fee) a rescore from their state boards, which, in turn, send the requests to NCEES. NCEES then sends the individual questions to SME's Professional Registration Committee for the actual rescoring. Part of the fee charged for this procedure is given to SME. </P>

<P>SME's Professional Registration Committee held its annual workshop on March 10, 1996 in Phoenix, AZ prior to the SME annual meeting. Committee members chose problems for the 9710 exam from the problem bank or agreed to write new ones. All the new problems for the 9710 exam are due at NCEES by July 16, 1996.</P>

<P>The 10 essay questions from the 9610 exam will be scored by the committee on Jan. 4, 1997 at SME Headquarters. The 10 multiple-choice questions will be scored by computer at NCEES.</P>

<P>The Study Guide for Professional Registration of Mining/Mineral Engineers has been completely revised. The volume contains information on state boards, NCEES, exam procedures, the mining/mineral syllabus and a complete sample exam. It currently sells for $25 per copy.  </P>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

