<HEAD>

<TITLE>GEM: Government, Education and Mining</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml>
<IMG SRC="art/gemlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

GEM</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5><CITE>Government, Education and Mining</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>The Government, Education and Mining (GEM) Program increases public awareness of the importance of minerals and mining to everyday life and our modern standard of living.  

<P>Established in 1975, the function of the GEM Program has been to translate technology to the lay public.  The National GEM Committee, comprised of 37 SME members, directs several national activities and provides liaison with SME local section GEM committees to assist with community outreach programs.  Program activities are carried out through six subcommittees: Communications, Education, Public Outreach, Materials, GEM Development and University Liaison.

<P>Both national and local activities bring SME members together with teachers, journalists, legislators and other professionals to foster mutual understanding and narrow the gap between the technological community and society at large. 

<HR>

<P>At the national level, GEM provides:

<UL>

<LI>Assistance to SME local section GEM committees with community outreach programs.

<LI>Annual GEM Awards to Individual SME members and SME local sections to recognize outstanding accomplishments and contributions to public education.

<LI>Monthly GEM Facts column in <I>Mining Engineering</I>: an information source about educational materials available and suggested local education activities.

<LI>Educational Materials for sale to SME members and teachers to assist in minerals education efforts.  Some free materials available ($3.50 postage/handling charge).

<LI>Video lending library available free to SME members. 

<LI>Teacher assistance: classroom speakers, factual information, hands-on activities, resource guides.

<LI>Minerals Education Coalition Exhibits at National Science Teachers Association (NSTA) conventions.

<LI>Special Awards presented to students at annual International Science and Engineering Fair (ISEF).

<LI>Annual Photo Contest with cash awards to promote the mining industry.

</UL>

<P>At the local level, GEM may provide:

<UL>

<LI>Speakers bureaus; professional geologists and engineers to conduct tours or classroom presentations.

<LI>Minerals Education Exhibits at teacher conventions and community events.

<LI>Mine and mill group tours.

<LI>Accredited workshops for science teachers.

</UL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to GEM Dept.</STRONG>.

</BODY>

