<TITLE>GEM: About GEM Facts</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml>
<IMG SRC="art/gemlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

GEM</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5><CITE>About GEM Facts</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P><B>GEM Facts</B> is a monthly feature column in SME's <I>Mining Engineering</I> magazine. Its purpose is to provide a forum for shared information about successful public education activities, upcoming national events, proposed legislation affecting SME members, and teaching materials available to members, teachers, and the general public.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left>

<DL>
<DT><H3>MII materials aid local GEM section</H3>
<DD>Linda Baltich, Colorado Section GEM chair, reports that the Mineral Information Institute (MII), located in Denver, CO, has been a great partner in many local GEM activities. Linda says, "MII often provides us with materials when we visit schools and do community outreach projects. MII posters and handouts are excellent resources."
<P>In return, SME provide the names and addresses of interested educators to MII. MII is available to help other GEM Committees. Contact Nelson Fugate or Jackie Evanger at 303-297-3226.
</DL>
<H4>Thanks for GEM financial support</H4>
<P>Our expression of appreciation goes out to those members who contributed to GEM along with their 1995 dues. Your generous support has helped us continue our efforts to educate the public about our constant and growing dependency on products made from minerals and to be a major part of creating a positive image of the mining and minerals industry.
<P><CITE>Gary D. Howell</CITE><BR>Executive Director
<P><CITE>Walter S. Lombardo</CITE><BR>1996/97 GEM Committee Chair

