<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#000088"><P>PLANT OPERATORS SYMPOSIUM</P></FONT>

<P>Format: Short presentations followed by open discussion (problems, suggestions, answers) 

on areas of major concern to plant operators &#173; from coal to precious metals.

<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#000088"><P>Sessions:</P></FONT>

<P><I>Operating: "Things that cause great operating headaches and problems."

<P>Maintenance and Modifications: "Why is there never enough time to do it right, but always enough time to do it wrong."

<P>People (two sessions): "Let's talk about the folks that really make our plants produce 24-hours a day, 7-days a week."

<P>Instrumentation and Process Control: "You mean someone is offering a control session that operators can use?"

<P>Open Session: "Finally, my chance to correct the wrongs of the metallurgical world."

</I><BR>

