<TITLE>Meetings Regsitration</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12>

Meetings:</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Registration Forms</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>Meetings registration and hotel-reservation forms are available on-line for your use in two different formats:

<UL>
<LI>The first is a pkZip-compressed PostScript file that can be uncompressed and downloaded into any PostScript printer; both <A HREF="postscript/REG.ZIP">Annual Meeting Registration</A> and <A HREF="postscript/HOTEL.ZIP">hotel-reservation</A> forms are available in this format.
<LI>The other online option is an Adobe Acrobat (".pdf") file, again for both <A HREF="pdfs/reg.pdf">Meetings Registration</A> and <A HREF="pdfs/hotel.pdf">Hotel-reservation</A> forms.
<DL>
<DD>To use the Acrobat forms, you must first download the <B>FREE</B> Adobe Acrobat Reader software, either from <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Acrobat/AcrobatWWW.html"><B>Adobe Systems' Web site</B></A> or one of the many mirror-sites they have listed there. This download is a "one-shot" operation: You need only download it once and install it, and from that point on you will be able to access Adobe Acrobat files on the World Wide Web.
</DL>
<LI>Alternately, you can <A HREF="feedback.stml">contact SME's Meetings Dept.</A> and have them mail the desired forms to you.
</UL>

