<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Publications: Ordering from SME (Under Contstruction)</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Publications</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Ordering from SME</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>The order form for SME's <A HREF="books/booklist.stml">Books</A> and <A HREF="memorabilia/index.stml">Specialty Merchandise</A> catalog is available on-line for your use in two different formats:

<UL>
<LI>The first is a <A HREF="postscript/ORDER.ZIP">pkZip-compressed PostScript file</A> that can be uncompressed and downloaded into any PostScript printer;
<LI>The other online option is an <A HREF="pdfs/order.pdf">Adobe Acrobat (".pdf") file</A>.
<DL>
<DD>To use the Acrobat forms, you must first download the <B>FREE</B> Adobe Acrobat Reader software, either from <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Acrobat/AcrobatWWW.html"><B>Adobe Systems' Web site</B></A> or one of the many mirror-sites they have listed there. This download is a "one-shot" operation: You need only download it once and install it, and from that point on you will be able to access Adobe Acrobat files on the World Wide Web.
</DL>
<LI>Alternately, you can <A HREF="feedback.stml">contact SME's Publication Sales Dept.</A> and have them mail the desired forms to you.
</UL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Customer Service</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>puborders.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
323.</P>

