<HEAD>

<TITLE>Internet Resources</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<IMG SRC="art/intlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12>

Internet Resources</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Links to Other Places</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>This listing of World Wide Web sites is far from complete, but it contains many points of interest. If you find a new site to include in this list, <B>let us know about it!</B>

<DL>

<DD><P><A
HREF="http://www.clas.ufl.edu/CLAS/Departments/Geology/"><B>University of
Florida, Department of Geology</B></A> - One of the few "wired" mining
departments in the United States.

<DD><P><A HREF='http://www.wateronline.com/'><B>Water Online</B></A> - a site that 
will include Pollution Online, HazMat Online, Engineers Online and Environment Online.

<DD><P><A HREF='http://www.offshore-technology.com/'><B>Offshore Technology</B></A> - 
a web-site for the offshore oil and gas industry with news on current projects and 
developments, contractors and suppliers guide, exhibitions and conference listings 
and an industry associations directory.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.tms.org"><B>TMS' Home Page</B></A> - The home page
for TMS, a member  society of AIME.

<DD>US Bureau of Mines (transferred functions):
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.alrc.doe.gov">Albany Research Center</A> (DOE)
<LI><A HREF="http://minerals.er.usgs.gov/minerals">Minerals Information</A> (DOE)
<LI><A HREF="http://www.usbm.gov">Pittsburgh and Spokane Research Centers</A> (Mining Health and Safety Research)
<LI><A HREF="http://speedy.usbm.gov:8000">USBM Research Publication Database</A> (NIOSH)
</UL>


<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.microserve.net/~doug"><B>Tensor's Mine Net</B></A>
- A mining and mineral engineering information gateway.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://lhl.lib.mo.us"><B>The Linda Hall Library</B></A> - 
The Linda Hall Library on the World Wide Web.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.uvision.com/"><B>Computer ESP</B></A> -
Information on more than 20,000 computer vendors and dealers and their products.  You
can browse by categories or search by keyword.  Once you find the product you're
looking for, you can set the price you're willing to buy or sell for.

<!-- End of General Computer Support Stuff section -->

<DD><P><A HREF="http://volcano.und.nodak.edu/"><B>Volcanoworld</B></A> -
Includes <A HREF="http://volcano.und.nodak.edu/vwdocs/msh/msh.html">a look at
Mount St. Helens</A>, an amazing look at the story of Mount St. Helens.  You will
be able to discover what happened before, during and after the awesome eruption
of May 18, 1980. See if <B>you</B> ever again feel that mankind is threatening
the planet.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.circus.com/~no_dhmo/"><B>The Coalition to Ban
Dihydrogen Monoxide</B></A> - This makes a <B>very</B> interesting comparison
with literature from some environmental-activist groups. Try
giving a copy of it to someone who doesn't know what dihydrogen monoxide is, see
if they agree with the basic ideas presented, and then explain to them that
dihydrogen monoxide is <B>water</B> (H2O).

<!-- End of Humorous and Unusual Items section -->

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.sierraclub.org"><B>The Sierra Club</B></A> - Often, a conflicting viewpoint.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.greenpeace.org"><B>GreenPeace</B></A> - Another often-conflicting viewpoint.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://http://www.cnn.com/"><B>CNN Interactive</B></A> - This
doesn't really need an explanation.  It's exactly what you'd expect.  Get all the
latest news as it's happening!

<DD><P><A HREF="http://www.usatoday.com/"><B>USA Today</B></A> - This site
has been around for a while, but it's recently added considerable content,and it's all
free.  Like the CNN site, this is a great place to get the latest news.  Who
knows how long these sites will remain free, but enjoy them while they last!


<DD><P><A HREF="http://okra.ucr.edu/okra/"><B>OKRA - net.citizen Directory
Service</B></A> - A service from University of California at Riverside that will
help you find e-mail addresses of individuals and organizations who are "wired."  The database is not complete but it's growing constantly, and
you can add to it.

<DD><P><A HREF="www.lookup.com/"><B>LookUP!</B></A> - An e-mail lookup
service.  Its database is not complete, but between LookUP! and OKRA (both free
services), you can often find that missing e-mail address.


<DD><P><A
HREF="http://home.mcom.com/home/internet-index.html"><B>Yahoo</B></A> - Both a
Web-searching and indexing facility, run by Netscape. It's good, and
allows you to make suggestions for items and URLs to include in its index. 

<DD><P><A
HREF="http://webcrawler.cs.washington.edu/WebCrawler/WebQuery.html"><B>Web
Crawler</B></A> - Another Web-search engine.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://lycos.cs.cmu.edu"><B>Lycos</B></A> - Another
Web-search engine, run by Carnegie-Mellon.

<DD><P><A
HREF="http://web.nexor.co.uk/public/aliweb/search/doc/form.html"><B>AliWeb</B></A>
- A search engine run by Nexor, from the United Kingdom. Nexor also runs the <A
HREF="http://pubweb.nexor.co.uk/public/cusi/doc/list.html"><B>CUSI</B></A> Web-index
service.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://wings.buffalo.edu/world/"><B>The Virtual Tourist World
Map</B></A> - Not really a <B>search</B> facility, but an interesting approach to
locating Internet resources; You start with the whole world, and click your way
through more and more precise maps to locate resources in a given geographical
area.

<DD><P><A HREF="http://gnn.digital.com/gnn/wic/index.html"><B>The Whole
Internet Catalog</B></A> - A fairly extensive index list of Internet resources
and a pretty good starting place for new browsers.

<DT>The following items were listed on one or more US Bureau of Mines pages. We've not 
yet had the opportunity to explore these links, but rather than lose them in the 
imminent Bureau shutdown, we've included them here.

<DT><H3> Mining Related </H3>
<DD>
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://www.ehnr.state.nc.us/EHNR/DLR/scr1.htm">North Carolina Geological Survey</A>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://gn.mines.colorado.edu:80/">Colorado School Of Mines</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.enn.com">Environmental News Network</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.info-mine.com/">Info-Mine Web</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.microserve.net/~doug/">MineNet</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.wimsey.com/Magnet/mc/index28.html">Mining Channel</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.nbmg.unr.edu">Nevada Bureau of Mines and Geology</a>
<li><a
HREF="HTTP://www.rahul.net/infodyn/rockhounds/rockhounds.html">Rockhounds
Information Page</A>
</UL>
<DT><H3>Federal Government Information</H3>
<DD>
<UL>
