<!-- Document Body Text -->

<P>This list is incomplete at best, and will be added to as more sites are brought to our attention. For the time being, browse around in here, and see what you can find:

<DT><DD><P><A HREF="http://www.lib.lsu.edu/gov/fedgov.html"><B>The US Government
Web index</B></A> - For finding Web-based (and other Internet-based) resources on
many of the divisions, branches and bureaus of the US Government.


<DT><DD><P><A HREF="http://thomas.loc.gov"><B>Thomas</B></A> - A
searchable resource for finding current (and possibly past or otherwise active)
US legislation on a number of subjects. Heartily recommended if there's a bill in
Congress that you're trying to follow.

<DT><DD>US Bureau of Mines (transferred functions):
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.alrc.doe.gov">Albany Research Center</A> (DOE)
