<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Meetings</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5><CITE>General Information</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text -->

<H3>ADVANCE  REGISTRATION DEADLINE:</H3>

<H4>FRIDAY, FEB. 23, 1996</H4>

<H2>Register Now!</H2>

<P>Please complete the <A HREF="mtgreg.stml">Advance Registration Form</A> and return no later than Feb. 23, 1996, to:

<P><B>MAIL:</B>

<P>SME, Meetings Dept.

<P>PO Box 625002

<P>Littleton CO 80162-5002

<P><B>PHONE:</B>

<P>800-763-3132, or 303-973-9550

<P><B>Fax:</B>

<P>303-979-3461

<P>Full payment MUST accompany the completed Advance Registration Form.

<P>When registering by phone or fax <STRONG>DO NOT SEND ANOTHER COPY BY MAIL.</STRONG>

<P>Confirmations listing your registration fees, activities and proceedings requested will be mailed to the individual. PLEASE CHECK THIS INFORMATION CAREFULLY.

<H3>FAX-ON-DEMAND SERVICE</H3>

<P>Get the information you need, when you need it. Call the SME Fax-on-Demand  service  from  a  touch-tone  phone  in  the  United States  and  Canada at 1-800-763-0083, all other countries 516-222-4933.

<H3>REGISTRATION FEES </H3>

<P>To receive the advance registration charge, SME must receive your registration form and payment by Feb. 23, 1996. After Feb. 23, 1996, on-site registration fees apply. One-day registration is available.

<H3>REGISTRATION POLICY</H3>

<P>All attendees and authors at the annual meeting are required to register. Nonmember authors may register at the member rate. The one-day fee is available only for the day you want to attend (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday). The appropriate badge is required for admittance to technical sessions and exhibit and will be checked at the entrances of all activities.

<H3>NONMEMBER REGISTRANTS</H3>

<P>Nonmember registrants (excluding one-day registrants) who join SME during the SME Annual Meeting will have their 1996 dues waived. 

<H3>STUDENT REGISTRATION POLICY</H3>

<P>Student registration for the 1996 SME Annual Meeting and Exhibit must meet eligibility requirements. SME requires that an individual must be attending a college/university/higher education institution on a full-time basis to qualify for student registration rates. SME cannot process student registrations without evidence that you are a full-time student. When sending your registration to SME, please provide registration confirmation from your educational institution. Student registrations without this information will not be processed.

<H3>REGISTRATION AT THE MEETING</H3>

<P>On-site registration will be conducted during the following hours in the North Plaza Lobby of the Phoenix Civic Plaza.

<P>Sunday, March 10, Noon to 5 p.m.

<P>Monday, March 11, 7 a.m. to 7 p.m.

<P>Tuesday, March 12, 7 a.m. to 5 p.m.

<P>Wednesday, March 13, 7 a.m. to 6:30 p.m.

<P>Thursday, March 14, 7 a.m. to 11 a.m.

<H3>REFUND POLICY</H3>

<P>If circumstances require you to cancel your SME registration, written notice must be sent to Meetings Dept., SME, PO  Box 625002, Littleton, CO 80162-5002, postmarked no later than Feb. 23, 1996. A $25.00 processing fee will be assessed on all total cancellations.

<P><STRONG>NO REFUNDS FOR REGISTRATION, SHORT COURSES, OR SOCIAL FUNCTION TICKETS WILL BE ISSUED AFTER THE FEB. 23 DEADLINE.</STRONG>

<H3>SHUTTLE BUS</H3>

<P>Best Western Executive Park, Hilton Suites, Holiday Inn Airport East, Holiday Inn North Central, Quality Hotel. (Shuttles will operate on 10-15 minute intervals, depending on distance and weather conditions)

<P>Sunday, March 10, 11:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m.

<P>Monday, March 11, 7 a.m. to 7:30 p.m.

<P>Tuesday, March 12, 7 a.m. to 6:30 p.m.

<P>Wednesday, March 13, 7 a.m. to 7:30 p.m.

<P>Thursday, March 14, 7 a.m. to Noon

<H3>AIRFARE AND CAR RENTAL DISCOUNTS </H3>

<P>Arrangements have been made with United and America  West Airlines and Alamo Rent-a-Car for special discounts for SME meeting attendees.

<H3>HOUSING INFORMATION</H3>

<P>Hotel accommodations are available at the Best Western Executive Park, Crowne Plaza, Hilton Suites, Holiday Inn Airport East, Holiday Inn North Central, Phoenix Hilton Suites, Hyatt Regency, Quality Inn, Ramada Inn, San Carlos. Please complete the Hotel Reservation form and return no later than Feb. 16, 1996 to: SME Housing Bureau, c/o Phoenix Valley of the Sun Convention Bureau, 400 E. Van Buren St., Ste. 600, Phoenix, AZ 85004-2290, fax 602-253-0417. A ONE NIGHT'S DEPOSIT BY CREDIT CARD MUST ACCOMPANY THE COMPLETED FORM.

<H3><A HREF="hotelcover.stml">HOTEL RESERVATION FORM</A></H3>

<P>Acknowledgments will be sent by the SME Housing Bureau and confirmations will be sent by the hotel. 

<H3>TECHNICAL SESSIONS</H3>

<P>All SME technical sessions will be conducted at the Phoenix Civic Plaza.

<H3>EXHIBIT HOURS </H3>

<P>Exhibitor products and services will be showcased at the 1996 SME annual exhibit located in Hall A/B/C of the Phoenix Civic Plaza. Badge is required for admittance.

<P>Monday, March 11, 4 p.m. to 7 p.m.

<P>Tuesday, March 12, 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.

<P>Wednesday, March 13, 10 a.m. to 6:30 p.m.


<H3>PUBLICATION SALES</H3>

<P>The SME Publication Sales will be located in  Hall A at the Phoenix CIvic Plaza. SME publications and preprints of the 1996 SME annual meeting will be available for purchase during the following hours:

<P>Sunday, March 10, Noon to 5 p.m.

<P>Monday, March 11, 8 a.m.  to 7 p.m.

<P>Tuesday, March 12, 8 a.m. to 5 p.m.

<P>Wednesday, March 13, 8 a.m. to 6:30 p.m.

<P>Thursday, March 14, 8 a.m. to 11 a.m.

<H3>ACKNOWLEDGMENTS</H3>

<P>The events of the convention will be supported by many generous corporate sponsors. All contributing firms receive a sponsorship ribbon for their staff as recognition of their support. All contributors will be acknowledged in the annual meeting pocket program and in the 1996 sponsors booklet. For further information, contact SME Meetings Manager, at 303-973-9550.

<H4>Sponsorship Opportunities:</H4>

<UL TYPE=disc>

<LI>Short Course Luncheon

<LI>SME Membership Kick-Off Event

<LI>Meeting Tote Bag Insertion Advertising

<LI>Technical Sessions

<LI>Symposia

<LI>Exhibit Hall Coffee Break

</UL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Meetings Dept.</STRONG>.

