<HR>

<CENTER><H1><I>Minerals - Serving the Global Community</I></H1></CENTER>

<P>Minerals are defined as naturally occurring substances obtained for man's use. The SME Annual Meeting Program Committee has dedicated the 1997 technical program to the global practice, science, and technology, applied in the pursuit of finding, obtaining, and processing minerals for the community of man.</P>

<P>The SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit is comprised of 4-5,000 corporate officers, operations and management professionals, operating and staff engineers and consultants engaged in mineral exploration, underground and surface mining, solution mining, rock mechanics, operations research, mineral processing and environment control. These professionals share their experience, skill, and know-how for the benefit of the industry. The following is a glimpse of 1997 highlights:</P>

<H2>Comminution Practices for the Next Century</H2>

<P>It is  a known fact the comminution process is energy intensive. It uses approximately 29 billion kwhr of electrical energy per annum for size reduction and an additional 3.7 billion kwhr per annum is contained energy in consumables such as grinding media and liners. Ever since the oil crisis of the 1970s the profitability of industries has been linked closely to efficient use of energy and the minerals industry is no exception. These facts have provided incentives for universities, government laboratories, and industries to conduct research in this important area of comminution. As a result, novel comminution devices and new process control strategies for control of mineral processing operations are being developed.</P>

<P>Other disciplines examined during the 1997 meeting include:
<UL>
<LI>Coal
<LI>Industrial Minerals
<LI>Mining & Exploration
<LI>Mineral & Metallurgical Processing
<LI>Minerals Resource Management
<LI>Society of Economic Geologists
</UL></P>


<HR>

<CENTER><H1>1997 SME PROGRAM COMMITTEE</H1></CENTER>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD><B>Chair<TD>Robert W. Schafer, BHP Minerals Intl. Inc.</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Coal Division<TD>Edward D. Doney, Kerr-McGee Coal Corp.</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Industrial Minerals Division<TD>Fred G. Heivilin, Oil-Dri Corp. of America</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Mining & Exploration Division<TD>William H. Wilkinson, Jr., Phelps Dodge Corp.</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Mineral & Metallurgical Processing Division<TD>S. Komar Kawatra, Michigan Technological University</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Minerals Resource Management Committee<TD>Bruce W. Cavender, Magma Copper Co.</TR>
<TR><TD><B>Society of Economic Geologists<TD>Stanley Hamilton</TABLE>

<HR>

<CENTER><H1>Who We Are and What We Do</H1></CENTER>

<P>The Society for Mining, Metallurgy, and Exploration Inc., advances the worldwide mining and minerals community through information exchange and professional development. SME is the technical organization for professionals in the minerals industry. SME members focus on increasing knowledge and skill within the profession. With more than 17,000 members in 25 countries, the Society continues to evolve in response to the changing needs of its members around the world. Through the benefits of publications, meetings, education and GEM program, SME is the minerals industry resource for the successful minerals professional.</P>

<P><B>SME</B> exists to provide timely, quality technical information to its members on a global level.</P>

<P><B>SME</B> provides reliable and credible mining and minerals information to those involved in the development of public policy.</P>

<P><B>SME</B> is the forum for leaders of international mining and minerals organizations to share and disseminate knowledge and information.</P>

<P><B>SME</B> is active in providing the public with an understanding of what mining and minerals mean for day-to-day life.</P>

<CENTER>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>The Society for Mining, Metallurgy, and Exploration Inc.</FONT><BR>
PO Box 625002, Littleton CO 80162-5002<BR>
8307 Shaffer Pkwy, Littleton, CO 80127-4102<BR>
800-763-3132, 303-973-9550<BR>
Fax: 303-979-3461<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com"><B>smenet@aol.com</B></A><BR>
Internet: <A HREF="http://www.smenet.org/"><B>http://www.smenet.org</B></A></P>
</CENTER>

<!--End body of text -->
