<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Merchandise: Educational Materials - Videos</TITLE><LINK REV=made HREF=mailto:smenet@aol.com></HEAD><BODY><H1><FONT SIZE=10><IMG SRC=../art/smelogo.GIF ALIGN=left><IMG SRC=../art/newlogo.GIF ALIGN=right>SME Merchandise:</FONT></H1><P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Educational Materials - Videos</FONT><HR></FONT></CITE></P><BR CLEAR=all><!-- Document Body Text --><H3><HR><IMG SRC="../art/commonground.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12>Videos</H3><P><A NAME="cground"><H4>"Common Ground"</I></H4> (26 minutes) Produced by Caterpillar. For Elementary to Adult audiences; stresses the importance of minerals and mining to our standard of living; covers history, environmental concerns, exploration, mine development, public perceptions and using public involvement as an educational tool (The <I>Common Ground</I> package includes a Teacher's Guide, User's Guide and "Modern Mining & You" informational booklet). Available in:<H4>VHS  Order No. 22-0905  $10</H4><H4>PAL  Order No. 22-0906  $10</H4></P><P><A HREF="misceducation.html#cground">Companion materials packages</A> are also available...</P><BR CLEAR=all><P><HR><H4>Out of the Rock</H4> (29 minutes) Produced by the US Bureau of Mines. For Jr. High to Adult audiences; examines the importance of minerals and mining; provides examples of minerals use in everything from glass to makeup to toothpaste to wiring. Discusses recycling and environmental issues. Available in:<H4>VHS  Order No. 22-0900  $10</H4><H4>PAL  Order No. 22-0901  $10</H4></P><P><HR><H4>Tierra de Todos (LAND of ALL)</H4> (<B>Spanish</B>; 26 minutes) Produced by Caterpillar. The story of modern mining in Latin America - tells of mining's products, advancement and increased concern for the environment. Visits a Dominican nickel mine, a llama farm in Chile, and the copper mining region of the Atacama desert. Available in:<H4>VHS  Order No. 22-0907  $10</H4><H4>PAL  Order No. 22-0909  $10</H4></P><P><HR><H4>Let's Do Mineral Science</H4> (30 minutes) Produced by the US Bureau of Mines. Demostrates six hands-on classroom activities to teach the mining process, the economics of mining, and from what minerals various products are made from. Activity worksheets included with this video. Available in:<H4> VHS only  Order No. 22-0908  $7</H4></P><BR CLEAR=all><P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left>Please feel free to <A HREF=mailto:smenet@aol.com>report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P></BODY></HTML>
