<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting General Information
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H2>General Information</H2>
</TH></TR></TABLE></FONT>

</FONT>

<!-- Common Header Information -->

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000"><TR><TH><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#ffffff"><B>
<H3>ADVANCE REGISTRATION DEADLINE:<BR>FRIDAY, FEBRUARY 7, 1997</H3>
</B></FONT></TH></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TD COLSPAN=6>
<H1>Register Now!</H1>

<P>Please complete the Advance Registration Form on the inside back cover and return no later than <B>February 7, 1997</B>, to:</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=12%><IMG SRC="art/mailicon.GIF"></TD>
<TD WIDTH=20%><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>MAIL:</B></FONT><BR>SME, Meetings Dept.<BR>PO Box 625002<BR>Littleton CO 80162-5002<BR CLEAR=left></TD>

<TD WIDTH=12%><IMG SRC="art/phoneicon.GIF"></TD>
<TD WIDTH=20%><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>PHONE:</B></FONT><BR>800-763-3132 <BR>or (303) 973-9550<BR CLEAR=left></TD>

<TD WIDTH=12%><IMG SRC="art/faxicon.GIF"></TD>
<TD WIDTH=20%><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>FAX:</B></FONT><BR>(303) 979-3461</TD>

</TR></TABLE>


<P><STRONG>Full payment MUST accompany the completed Advance Registration Form.</STRONG></P>

<P>When registering by phone or fax <B>DO NOT SEND ANOTHER COPY BY MAIL.</B></P>

<P>Confirmations listing your registration fees, activities and proceedings requested will be mailed to the individual. <B>PLEASE CHECK THIS INFORMATION CAREFULLY.</B></P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>FAX-ON-DEMAND SERVICE</FONT></H2>

<P>Get the information you need, when you need it. Call the SME Fax-on-Demand  service  from  a  touch  tone  phone  in the US and Canada at <B>1-800-763-0083</B>, all other countries <B>516-222-4933</B>.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>REGISTRATION FEES</FONT></H2>

<P>To receive the advance registration charge SME <B>must</B> receive your registration form and payment by February 7, 1997. <B>After</B> February 7, 1997, on-site registration fees apply. One-day registration is available.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>REGISTRATION POLICY</FONT></H2>

<P>All attendees and authors at the Annual Meeting are required to register. Nonmember authors may register at the member rate. The one-day fee is available only for the day you want to attend (Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday or Thursday). The appropriate badge is required for admittance to technical sessions and exhibit and will be checked at the entrances of all activities.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>NONMEMBER REGISTRANTS</FONT></H2>

<P>Nonmember registrants (excluding one-day registrants) who join SME during the SME Annual Meeting may be entitled to have their 1997 dues waived. See page 21 for further details.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>AIME</FONT></H2>

<P>The 126th AIME Annual Meeting is held in conjunction with the 1997 SME Annual Meeting. All AIME committee meetings and social activities will be held at the Hyatt Regency Hotel. Questions regarding AIME events should be directed to Arlene Pitilon, AIME headquarters, 345 East 47th St., New York, NY 10017, 212-705-7677.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>WAAIME</FONT></H2>

<P>The Woman's Auxiliary to AIME offers a special program of social functions. A <B>separate</B> check covering WAAIME registration fees and WAAIME social functions should be sent to: WAAIME, 345 East 47th St., 14th Floor, New York, NY 10017. Only members of WAAIME are entitled to register at the member registration rate. <B>Membership in AIME does not automatically make the spouse a member of WAAIME. </B>Nonmembers are welcome to register and attend these functions, and are invited to join WAAIME for only one additional dollar including 1997-98 dues. Registration packets will be mailed to individuals when registrations are postmarked no later than January 30, 1997. Registrants who do not receive their packets by return mail should contact WAAIME registration at the Colorado Registration Desk of the Marriott Hotel. Please note: Gentlemen are welcome to participate in the WAAIME program of social functions.</P>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Cancellations:</B></FONT>Request for cancellation must be in writing and postmarked no later than January 30, 1997. A $5.00 fee is assessed for all WAAIME refunds. Requests should be mailed to: WAAIME, 345 E. 47th St., 14th Floor, New York, NY 10017.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>STUDENT REGISTRATION POLICY</FONT></H2>

<P>Student registration for the 1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit must meet eligibility requirements. SME requires that an individual <I>must be attending a college/university/higher education institution on a full-time basis to qualify for student registration rates. </I>SME cannot process student registrations without evidence that you are a full-time student. When sending your registration to SME, please provide registration confirmation from your educational institution. Student registrations without this information will not be processed.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>REGISTRATION AT THE MEETING</FONT></H2>

<P>On-site registration will be conducted during the following hours in Lobby B of the Colorado Convention Center.

<TABLE>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Sunday, February 23</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>Noon - 5 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Monday, February 24</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 7 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Tuesday, February 25</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 5 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Wednesday, February 26</B></FONT></TD>	<TD>7 AM - 6:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Thursday, February 27</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 11 AM</TD>
</TR></TABLE></P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>REFUND POLICY</FONT></H2>

<P>If circumstances require you to cancel your SME registration, <B>written notice</B> must be sent to Meetings Dept., SME, PO  Box 625002, Littleton, CO 80162-5002, postmarked no later than February 7, 1997. A $25.00 processing fee will be assessed on all total cancellations.</P>

<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>NO REFUNDS FOR REGISTRATION, SHORT COURSES, OR SOCIAL FUNCTION TICKETS WILL BE ISSUED AFTER THE FEBRUARY 7 DEADLINE.</B></FONT>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>AIRFARE & CAR RENTAL DISCOUNTS</FONT></H2>

<P>Arrangements have been made with United Airlines and Alamo Rent-a-Car for special discounts for SME meeting attendees. Refer to the announcement.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>EXHIBIT HOURS</FONT></H2>

<P>Exhibitor products and services will be showcased at the 1997 SME Annual Exhibit located in Hall A/B of the Colorado Convention Center. Badge required for admittance.
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Monday, February 24</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>4 PM - 7 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Tuesday, February 25</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>10 AM - 5 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Wednesday, February 26</B></FONT></TD>	<TD>10 AM - 6:30 PM</TD>
</TR></TABLE></P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>SHUTTLE BUS</FONT></H2>

<P>Adam's Mark, Comfort Inn, Embassy Suites, Executive Tower, Holiday Inn, Hyatt Regency, and Marriott City Center. (Shuttles will operate on 10-20 minute intervals, depending on distance and weather conditions).
<TABLE>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Sunday, February 23</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>11:30 AM - 5:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Monday, February 24</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 7:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Tuesday, February 25</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 6:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Wednesday, February 26</B></FONT></TD>	<TD>7 AM - 7:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>SME Dinner Schedule</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>9 PM - 11:30 PM</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Thursday, February 27</B></FONT></TD>		<TD>7 AM - 12:30 PM</TD>
</TR></TABLE>
</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>HOUSING INFORMATION</FONT></H2>

<P>Hotel accommodations are available at the Adam's Mark, Comfort Inn, Embassy Suites, Executive Tower, Holiday Inn, Hyatt Regency, Marriott City Center hotels. Please complete the Hotel Reservation form on the inside front cover and return no later than <B>January 31, 1997</B> to: AIME/SME Housing Bureau, c/o Denver Convention & Visitors Bureau, 1555 California St., Ste. 300, Denver, CO 80202-4252, fax (303) 892-1636. <B>A ONE NIGHT DEPOSIT BY CREDIT CARD MUST ACCOMPANY THE COMPLETED HOTEL RESERVATION FORM.</I> Acknowledgments will be sent by the AIME/SME Housing Bureau and confirmations will be sent by the hotel. For detailed information on each hotel refer to hotel information.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>TRANSPORTATION OPTIONS FROM DIA</FONT></H2>

<P>Once you arrive at DIA, a complete ground transportation center is available and located on the fifth level of the main terminal, near baggage claim. All transportation companies have their booths located on this level and passengers catch their van, shuttle and taxis through the fifth level doors next to baggage claim.
<TABLE>
<TR><TH COLSPAN=2>The transportation services available are:</TH></TR>
<TD VALIGN=top><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>SuperShuttle</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN=top>
(303) 342-5454, (800) Blue-Van<BR>
$15.00 one-way<BR>
$27.00  round trip</TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN=top><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>The Airporter</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN=top>
(303) 333-5833<BR>
$15.00 one-way<BR>
$30.00  round trip</TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN=top><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Denver Express</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN=top>
(303) 766-7959<BR>
$15.00 one-way<BR>
$27.00  round trip</TD></TR></TABLE>
</P>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Taxi Companies:</B></FONT> A taxi fare to or from DIA ranges between $35.00 - $42.00 excluding tip. Shared ride programs are available through all taxi companies. The company names are Metro Taxi, Yellow Taxi, American Cab Company, Zone Cab, and Freedom Cab.</P>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Directions from DIA to downtown Denver for drive-in vehicles is:</B></FONT> Once exiting DIA you will be on Pena Boulevard. Stay on Pena Boulevard (approximately 11 mi.) to I-70 <I>West</I>. Take I-70 West to I-25 South. Take I-25 South to the 20th Street exit. Turn left on 20th. Continue on 20th to Blake Street (Coor's Field will be on your left). Turn right on Blake Street and continue to 17th Street. Turn left on 17th Street. All downtown hotels are located between 18th and 14th Streets.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>TECHNICAL SESSIONS</FONT></H2>

<P>All SME technical sessions will be conducted at the Colorado Convention Center.</P>

<H2><FONT FACE='Geneva,Arial'>PUBLICATION SALES</FONT></H2>

<P>The SME Publication Sales will be located in Lobby B of the Colorado Convention Center. SME publications and preprints of the 1997 Annual Meeting will be available for purchase during the following hours:
