<H1>AIME<BR>Highlights</H1>
<P>AIME 126th<BR>Annual Meeting</P>
<P>February 24-27<BR>Denver, Colorado</TH></FONT>

<TD BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<H1>KEYNOTE SESSION</H1>
<P>Monday, February 24<BR>
2 PM<BR>
Colorado Convention Center<BR>
<H3><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B><I>"Corporate Perspectives on a Global Mineral Industry"</I></B></FONT></H3>

<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#008737"><B>Moderator:</B></FONT> Simon Strauss, New Rochelle, NY</P>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#008737"><B>Panel:</B></FONT><UL>
<LI>Robert Smith, President  and Chief Operating Officer, Barrick Gold Corporation, Toronto, Ont., Canada
<LI>David Whitehead, Executive Director, Business Development, Billiton International, BV, Leidchendam, The Netherlands
</UL>

<H3><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#008737"><B>BANQUET & AWARDS CEREMONY</B></FONT></H3>
<P><IMG SRC="art/Gentry.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=6 WIDTH=124 HRIGHT=124 ALT="[D. Gentry]">
Monday, February 24<BR>
Cash Bar Reception: 6:30 PM<BR>
Banquet: 7:30 PM<BR>
Imperial Ballroom, Hyatt Regency Hotel<BR>
Tickets: $60 per person, $600 table of ten</P>

<P><CITE>1996 AIME President Donald W. Gentry serves as Master of Ceremonies for presentation of the Institute's major awards followed by a brief address by incoming 1997 AIME President Leonard G. Nelson. Music is featured throughout dinner. Black tie or dark business suits are appropriate attire for gentlemen.</CITE></P>

<H3><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial" COLOR="#008737"><B>AWARDS</B></FONT></H3>
<P>The following awards are presented:</P>
<P>AIME Distinguished Service Award, AIME Honorary Membership, James Douglas Gold Medal, Benjamin F. Fairless Award, Anthony F. Lucas Gold Medal, Robert Earll McConnell Award, Rossiter W. Raymond Award, Charles F. Rand Memorial Gold Medal, Environmental Conservation Distinguished Service Award, Mineral Economics Award, Mineral Industry Education Award, Hal Williams Hardinge Award, Erskine Ramsay Medal, Robert H. Richards Award, and the William Lawrence Saunders Medal.</P>

<P>For more information contact: Ms. Arlene Pitilon, AIME</P>
<P>14th Floor, 345 47th Street<BR>
New York, NY 10017-2304<BR>
Tel:	212-705-7677<BR>
Fax:	212-371-9622.</P>

<P><CITE>Held in conjunction with the SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit.</CITE></P>

