<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<TR><TH BGCOLOR="#008737" WIDTH=150 VALIGN=top>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H1>SME/AIME<BR>Keynote<BR>Session</H1>
<P>Monday<BR>February 24<P>2 PM<P>Colorado<BR>Convention<BR>Center</TH></FONT>

<TD BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><FONT SIZE=7 COLOR="#008737">T</FONT><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">he Business perspective of the Minerals Industry is broadening to meet the increasing demands of both the industrialized nations as well as the emerging economies of the Third World. The speakers for the 1997 SME/AIME Keynote Session will address how business strategies of mineral producers are evolving to achieve corporate growth objectives while bringing responsible business and operating practices to a world where markets are expanding, trade barriers are dropping, and laws are changing to encourage foreign investment.

<UL>

<B><FONT COLOR="#008737"><LI>Robert Smith, President of Barrick Gold Corporation</FONT></B> will describe how Barrick's corporate strategy has evolved with the company's success, particularly with respect to its expansion outside of North America. Mr. Smith will address how Barrick has managed business, social, political and environmental risks associated with its international operating successes, while learning to work within new social and business cultures.

<B><FONT COLOR="#008737"><LI>David Whitehead, Executive Director for Business Development at Gencor-Billiton</FONT></B> will look at the way in which South Africa's Gencor became an international mining house with multi-commodity impact by acquiring Billiton Minerals from Royal Dutch-Shell in 1995. Mr. Whitehead will present a non-North American perspective on the international nature of the minerals business, some insights into expectation for the future, and thoughts on the risks and rewards associated with international mineral ventures.

<B><FONT COLOR="#008737"><LI>Simon Strauss, Keynote Session Moderator</FONT></B> will open with a discussion of the awakening of the North American minerals business to foreign opportunities.

</UL>

</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Meetings Department</STRONG>.

