<HEAD>
<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting Education Forum
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I>Education Forum</I></H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#ffffff" CELLPADDING=6 BORDER=0>
<TR><TD BGCOLOR="#008737">
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>1997 SME<BR>ANNUAL MEETING<BR><BR>DENVER<BR>COLORADO</FONT></TD>
<TD>
<FONT FACE="Courier,Courier New" SIZE=7>Education Forum</FONT>

<CENTER>

<H1><CITE>
Educating Engineers for the<BR>
21st Century:<BR>
Perspectives of Entry-Level Engineers</CITE></H1>

<FONT COLOR="008737">
<H2>Sunday, February 23, 1997</H2>
<H3>6-8 PM * Salon E * Marriott Hotel * Denver, Colorado</H3>

<H3>Coordinators:<BR>
Virginia McLemore<BR>
R. Larry Grayson</H3>
</FONT>
</CENTER>

<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<P>
Last year's Education Forum focused on strengthening the exchange between industry and academia concerning the educational needs of entry-level professionals graduating into minerals engineering careers. The new format was informative and successful in attaining industrial perspectives from a cross-section of senior executives. At our next Forum, recent graduates will share their early experiences in industry and relate them to the level of their academic preparation. Substantial time will be planned for discussion between former students and educators. Please join representatives from industry and academia at the reception following the Forum to pursue topics of interest.
</P>
</FONT>


<CENTER>
<H3><FONT COLOR="#008737">
Reception will follow immediately.<BR>
8-10 PM * Salon F * Marriott Hotel</FONT></H3>
</TD></TR></TABLE> 

