<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Students: Student-Related Financial Policies</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Students</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Student-Related Financial Policies</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DT><H3>Student Meeting Registration Fees</H3><DT>

<DD>The Student Member/Student Nonmember registration fees for the SME Annual Meeting and Exhibit are set at 10% of the member/nonmember registration fees, rounded to the nearest $5. Because registration fees at other society meetings may include costs for such items as a proceedings and social functions, student registration fees for society <B><A HREF="mtgcalendar.stml">meetings</A></B> other than the annual meeting vary.

<DT><H3>Student <A HREF="scindex.stml">Short Course</A> Registration Fees</H3><DT>

<DD>Students may register for an SME short course at 35% off the member registration fee, on a space-available basis.

<DT><H3>Student Member Prices for <A HREF="publications.stml">Publications</A></H3><DT>

<DD>Reduced prices are available to SME Student Members for most SME publications. Each Student Member may purchase one copy of a publication at the Student Member rate.

<DT><H3>Student Chapter Financial Policies</H3><DT>

<DL><DT><H4><A HREF="make_chapter.stml">Student Chapter Start-up</A></H4><DT>

<DD>Upon obtaining official Student Chapter status, the Student Chapter receives $75 to assist with the initial conduct of its business.

<DT><H4>Student Chapter Rebates</H4><DT>

<DD>To be eligible for a rebate, the SME Student Chapter is required to submit an annual report to SME headquarters, and to have a minimum of 15 SME Student Members by the end of the calendar year. A Student Chapter with 15-25 Student Members receives $25. A Student Chapter with more than 25 SME Student Members receives $1 per member.

<DT><H4>Student Chapter Travel Allowance</H4><DT>

<DD>An allowance for SME Student Members who have traveled to SME meetings is available to each SME Student Chapter. The allowance is 5 per mile per SME Student Member, with a maximum of $1000 per Student Chapter per academic year. To receive the allowance, a Student Member travel report must be completed following attendance at an SME meeting and returned to SME headquarters. 

</DL>

<DT><H3>Student Contest Financial Policies</H3><DT>

<DD>Click for information on <B><A HREF="students_papers.stml">SME Student Contests</A></B>, including information on award money and travel allowances.

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Education Department</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>student_finance.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
102.</P>

