<TITLE>Membership: How to Become a Student Member of SME</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left height=65 width=68 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>How to Become a Student Member of SME</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DT><H3>SME Student Membership</H3>

<DD>Joining SME as a student member is one of the most important things you can do to enhance your professional development and career opportunities.  Click here for information on more <B><A HREF="benefits_student.stml">benefits</A></B> of SME student membership.


<DT><H3>Qualifications</H3>

<DD>A student in good standing at a minerals school who has been sponsored by an instructor (preferably an SME member) may join SME as a Student Member.


<DT><H3>Dues</H3>

<DD>Dues are established by the SME Board of Directors, and are currently set at only $15 per year.  If a student joins SME during the fall semester, the dues cover the remainder of the year plus the entire following year.


<DT><H3>Membership Application</H3>

<DD>To apply for membership, contact us for an application.  Call 800-763-3132 or 303-973-9550, fax 303-973-3845, or e-mail to <B><A HREF=mailto:smenet@aol.com>smenet@aol.com</A></B>.


</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

