<HEAD>

<TITLE>Membership: Outstanding Student Paper Contest Guidelines</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html" TARGET="_top">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Outstanding Student Paper Contest Guidelines</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DD>

<P>Each year SME sponsors two Outstanding Student Paper Contests, an Undergraduate Division contest and a Graduate Division contest. The Undergraduate Division is open only to SME Student Members.  The Graduate Division is open to all members of SME working toward an advanced degree.  These contests reflect the society's dedication to educational and scientific programming to benefit the public and profession in its understanding of the economic production and utilization of mineral resources.</P>

<P>Papers submitted in a contest are judged equally on preparation, presentation, and technical merit.  Preparation includes research effort, diversity of source information, and knowledge of subject.  Presentation includes organization and development of material, language, and reader contact.  Technical merit includes contribution, scope, and overall accuracy.</P>

<P>Each division winner is awarded $500, a certificate of recognition, a travel allowance to attend the SME Annual Meeting not to exceed $250, and one ticket to the function at which the cash award and certificate are to be presented.  In addition, the winner is acknowledged in Mining Engineering magazine, and the winning paper is considered for publication in the magazine.</P>

<P>To be eligible for the contest, the paper must be submitted by the student's Faculty Advisor and <B>received</B> by <B><I>December 1</I></B>.</P>

<H2>Guidelines for Preparing a Paper</H2>

<OL>

<LI>The paper should be prepared by one author and should be the original work of that author as much as possible.  A portion, such as a chapter, from the author's thesis or dissertation is not acceptable as a contest entry.  The paper should not have been published previously.

<LI>The paper should be on the subject of geology, geophysics, mineral processing, mining, or a related area.  

<LI>The paper should be typed, single-spaced, on <B><I>no more than six</I></B> 8 1/2" x 11" pages.  <B><I>Papers not conforming to these restrictions will be disqualified</I></B>.

<LI>Illustrations should be pertinent, neat, and suitable for reproduction.

<LI>The paper should conform to the SME bibliography style (guide follows).

<LI>The cover page should contain the following information:

<BR>Title of Paper

<BR>Author's Name

<BR>School affiliation

<BR>Author's Mailing Address

<BR>Author's SME Member Number

<BR>Division of contest in which paper is to be entered

<BR>Current Date

</OL>

<H2>Instructions for Submitting Paper</H2>

<OL>

<LI>Upon completion, the paper should be given to the Faculty Advisor with a request that it be submitted in the appropriate Division of the SME Outstanding Student Paper Contest.

<LI>The Faculty Advisor should provide the following information when submitting the paper:

<BR>Author's Name

<BR>Title of Paper

<BR>Author's Student Status (undergraduate/graduate) when paper was prepared

<BR>Current Date

<BR>Faculty Advisor's Name

<BR>Faculty Advisor's School Address

<LI>The paper should be <B>received</B> by <B><I>December 1</I></B>.

</OL>

<P>Student Contests

<BR>Society for Mining, Metallurgy,

<BR>and Exploration (SME), Inc.

<BR>8307 Shaffer Parkway

<BR>Littleton, CO  80127-4102  USA</P>

<P>For clarification or additional information, contact the Education Dept. at SME headquarters at (800) 763-3132, (303) 973-9550, fax (303) 973-3845, or <B>e-mail <A HREF="smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A></B>.

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>student_papers.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
139.</P>

