<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Students: Outstanding Student Chapter Contest Guidelines</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Students</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Outstanding Student Chapter Contest Guidelines</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL><DT>

<DD>Each year since 1967, SME has recognized the most outstanding student chapter. This award is one of high distinction because it is evidence that a chapter has conducted its business in a professional manner. Since 1979, the award has been based on a review of annual reports of the Student Chapters. 

<P>The winning SME Student Chapter receives an award of $500, a certificate of recognition, and one ticket to the awards banquet at the SME annual meeting. The chapter receives a travel allowance up to $250 to send a representative to the annual meeting. The award is presented at the awards banquet by the SME president. Three runners-up receive certificates of recognition. All winners will be recognized in <I><A HREF=me.stml">Mining Engineering</A></I> magazine.</P>

<DT><H3>The Annual Report</H3>

<DD>To enter the Student Chapter contest or receive rebate assistance, each Student Chapter is required to prepare an annual report. Annual reports must be <I>received</I> by Dec. 1 to be included in the Student Chapter contest, or mailed by Dec. 31 to qualify for the rebate. 

<P>The Annual Report not only provides an historical record of Student Chapter activities, but also encourages professional accountability. There is no established format for the annual report; however, the following material may be included:</P>

<UL>

<LI>Membership (identification of Student Chapter officers, members, Faculty Sponsor and Section Counselor)

<LI>Student Chapter activities (sequential listing of activities including a description of the program in paragraph or outline form, and attendance information)

<LI>Student Member activities (sequential listing of activities including descriptions, names of participants, and, if appropriate, results of participation)

<LI>Treasurer's report

<LI>Secretary's report

<LI>Miscellaneous (photographs, etc. as documentation of special events)

</UL>

<P>To be eligible for the contest, the Annual Report must be <STRONG><I>no more than 50 pages</STRONG></I>, and must be <STRONG><I>received</I> by December 1</STRONG>.  The report should be loose-leaf bound. The Student Chapter should retain one copy of the report for its records; <STRONG>seven</STRONG> copies should be mailed to:</P>

Education Dept.<BR>SME<BR>8307 Shaffer Pkwy.<BR>Littleton, CO  80127-4102</P>

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Education Department</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>student_chapters.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
114.</P>

