<HEAD>

<TITLE>Membership: Notes from Around the World</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">

<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html" TARGET="_top">

<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Notes from Around the World</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<H2>Notes from Around the World</H2>

<UL>

<LI>Congratulations to students at Fort Lewis College in Durango, Colorado!  The SME Board of Directors approved their application to form an SME Student Chapter, making the Fort Lewis Student Chapter of SME the 33rd SME Student Chapter.

<LI>Students at the University of Texas-Austin and the University of Tarkwa, in Ghana, are working on forming SME Student Chapters at their universities.  Find out how to <B><A HREF="student_chaps.stml">form a student chapter </A></B>at your school!

<LI>An updated career information booklet is fresh off the presses!  This booklet describes specific professions in the minerals industry and basic qualifications.  Call 303-973-9550 or 800-763-3132, fax 303-973-3845, or e-mail <B><A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com</A></B> to request your copy.

<LI>Plans for the 1997 Students Forum are underway.  The '97 Forum will be planned by students and headquarters staff.  Send your ideas and comments to <B><A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">smenet@aol.com.</A></B>

<LI>Get ready now for the <B><A HREF="student_papers.stml">Outstanding Student Paper</A></B> and <B><A HREF="student_chapters.stml">Outstanding Student Chapter</A></B> contests.  Entries must be received by December 1.

<LI>The Accreditation Board for Engineering and Technology (<A HREF="accreditation.stml">ABET</A></B>) is rewriting the criteria for accreditation of engineering programs in the US.  SME has written new criteria for <B><A HREF="mincrit.stml">mining engineering</A></B> and <B><A HREF="geprog.stml">geological engineering</A></B> programs.  Your input is welcome.

</UL>

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to Member Services</STRONG>.

