<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Students: How to Form an SME Student Chapter</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

Membership</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>How to Form an SME Student Chapter</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DT>

<DD>A Student Chapter of SME may be organized at any educational institution of higher learning where there is an existing program in a technical area associated with SME, and where there is sufficient student enrollment and interest.  Sponsorship shall be provided by the Local Section in the area where the Student Chapter is located; if there is no Local Section, sponsorship shall be provided by the Society.  For a Student Chapter to be affiliated with SME, approval of the SME Board of Directors is required.

<P>The Local Section shall designate an SME member, preferably someone employed by industry or government, to serve as Section Counselor.  At the educational institution, a member of the faculty, preferably an SME member, shall be designated to serve as Faculty Sponsor.  The Section Counselor and Faculty Sponsor shall promote contact between professionals and students and provide guidance and support for the Student Chapter program.

<P>Student Chapter governance shall comply with the Articles of Incorporation and Bylaws of SME and regulations of the associated educational institution.  Within the constraints outlined, the Student Chapter shall conduct and be responsible for its business and administration and report annually on its activities to SME headquarters.

<P>When it has been determined that the SME-associated educational program is permanent and that there is serious interest among students and faculty, the following steps should be taken:

<OL>

<LI>Identify a member of the faculty, preferably an SME member, to serve as Faculty Sponsor.

<LI>Contact the Chairman of the SME Local Section in the area and request Student Chapter sponsorship.  If no SME Local Section exists, contact the SME Education Dept.

<LI>Request that the SME Local Section (or SME) designate an SME member, preferably someone employed in industry or government, to serve as Section Counselor.

<LI>Draft Student Chapter Bylaws.

<LI>Elect Student Chapter Officers.  Note:  Officers must be members of SME or another member society of AIME.

<LI>Compile the following information:

<UL>

<LI>Student Chapter Bylaws

<LI>A completed Student Chapter information form

<LI>A letter prepared by the Faculty Sponsor indicating willingness to serve

<LI>A letter prepared by the Section Counselor indicating willingness to serve

</UL>

<LI>Forward the above documents, along with a request for SME affiliation, to the Local Section Chairman and/or SME Education Dept.

</OL>

<P>The request for affiliation will be reviewed at SME headquarters, and a recommendation regarding affiliation will be made to the SME Board of Directors.  The Student Chapter will be notified of the Board's decision.</P>

<P>If you have questions regarding Student Chapter formation, contact the Education Dept. at SME, PO Box 625002, Littleton, CO  80162-5002 800-763-3132, or 303-973-9550, fax 303-973-3845, or e-mail <B><A HREF=mailto:smenet@aol.com>smenet@aol.com</A></B>.</P>

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Education Department</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>make_chapter.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
86.</P>

</BODY>

