<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Students: Accreditation Support</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Students</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Support the Accreditation Process</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DT><H3>How You Can Support the Accreditation Process</H3>

<DD>Get involved!  Industry professionals are best qualified to determine the current and future specialized needs in their field.  Attend the meetings of the Accreditation and Curricular Issues subcommittee and the Council of Education and Accreditation (see below for more information).

<P>SME is continually seeking qualified program evaluators. Women, minority and industrial program evaluators are in particular demand. Click for information on <B><A HREF="program_eval.stml">how to nominate a program evaluator.</A><B/></P>

<P>Encourage your company to support its employees who become involved. The community is best served when a balance of professionals are involved in the accreditation process, visiting accredited programs and deciding on accreditation requirements.</P>

<P>Support colleges and universities with mining-related accredited programs. Educational programs prepare students for professional practice.</P>

<P>Encourage your employees and colleagues to become SME members. Professional societies support the objectives of the profession and its companies.</P>


<DT><H3>Current ABET Issues</H3>

<DD><B><A HREF="http://www.abet.ba.md.us">ABET</A></B> has been challenged to encourage innovation and creativity in individual engineering programs. To meet this challenge, many changes have been made in the last few years. These include a less-rigid requirement for the balance between engineering design and engineering topics, a move to an outcomes assessment approach, and a proposed simplification of the criteria. These revised criteria will need careful study by all parties involved in the accreditation process, and will also require an overhaul of <B><A HREF="geprog.stml"> geological engineering</A><B/> and <A HREF="mincrit.stml">mining engineering</A><B/> program criteria. Get involved in this process by contacting SME with your input, or by getting involved with SME's Accreditation and Curricular Issues subcommittee or Council of Education and Accreditation.


<DT><H3>SME's Accreditation and Curricular Issues Committee</H3>

<DD>The Accreditation and Curricular Issues subcommittee is responsible for creating program criteria for <B><A HREF="geprog.stml"> geological engineering</A><B/>, <A HREF="mincrit.stml">mining engineering</A><B/>, and mining engineering technology programs, and for ratifying ABET's general criteria, which must be met by all accredited engineering programs in the United States. By participating in this committee's open deliberations, you can have a direct effect on the accreditation requirements for schools across the United States. The committee meets at SME's annual meeting, held each year in February or March.


<DT><H3>Council of Education and Accreditation</H3>

<DD>The Council ratifies the actions of the Accreditation and Curricular Issues subcommittee. It directs the education activities of SME as they relate to students and accreditation. Get involved in this important process!

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Education Department</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>support_accreditation.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
120.</P>

</BODY>

