<HEAD>

<TITLE>SME Students: Program Evaluators</TITLE>

<LINK REV="made" HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">

</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H1><FONT SIZE=10>

<A HREF="membership.stml">
<IMG SRC="art/campus.GIF" ALIGN=right width=65 height=66 HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

<A HREF="index.html">
<IMG SRC="art/smelogo.GIF" ALIGN=left HSPACE=12 BORDER=0></A>

SME Students</FONT>

</H1>

<P><CITE><FONT SIZE=5>Program Evaluators</FONT><HR></FONT>

</CITE></P>

<P><CENTER><A HREF="http://rainbow.rmii.com/~pubs/navigator.html"><IMG SRC="art/navbtn.GIF" BORDER=0></A></P></CENTER>

<BR CLEAR=all>

<!-- Document Body Text --> <DL>

<DL>

<DT><H3>Program Evaluator Qualifications</H3>

<DD>A program evaluator must have had substantial experience in engineering or engineering technology and must have demonstrated an interest in engineering or engineering technology education. Academic members shall also have had experience in ABET-accredited engineering or engineering technology programs. An advanced degree in the field is not a requirement.

<DT><H3>How to Nominate a Program Evaluator</H3>

<DD>To nominate a program evaluator, send your name, address, and business phone, and the nominee's name, mailing address, business phone, fax, and e-mail address (if available), to SME Education Dept., PO Box 625002, Littleton, CO  80162-5002, or call 303-973-9550 or 800-763-3132, fax 303-973-3845, or e-mail <B><A HREF=mailto:smenet@aol.com>smenet@aol.com</A></B>.  

<P>Specify which curricular area(s) your nomination covers: environmental engineering, environmental engineering technology, geological engineering, geophysical engineering, metallurgical engineering, metallurgical engineering technology, mineral engineering, mineral processing engineering, mining engineering, or mining engineering technology.  Please nominate each individual for all the curricular areas for which he or she is qualified.</P>

<DT><H3>Requirements of Program Evaluators</H3>

<DD>Program evaluators are required to make a substantial commitment of time and energy to the accreditation process.  A general evaluation visit of an institution takes about seven days of concentrated effort, including preparation, the actual visit, and follow-up. Interim or focused visits may require less time.  

<P>Because of the nature of the team selection process, SME must always have many more evaluators available than will actually participate on visiting teams in any particular year.  However, each program evaluator should be available to participate on at least one accreditation visit per year.</P>

<P>Program evaluators must complete initial training and thereafter attend training at least every two years.  SME provides free training each year in conjunction with the annual meeting in February or March. Participation as an observer on a visiting team is also required. Although <B><A HREF="http://www.abet.ba.md.us">ABET<A/><B/> reimburses the travel expenses for evaluators who are part of a visiting team, observers must pay there own way. Limited funds from SME are available to assist with these expenses when necessary.</P>

</DL>

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Education Department</STRONG>.

<P><CITE>program_eval.stml</CITE><BR>Version 1.0</P>
<P>You are visitor number
131.</P>

</BODY>

