<TITLE>

APCOM: 

26th APCOM Table of Contents

</TITLE>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#a6a6a6">



<TABLE WIDTH=100%>

<TR>

<TD><IMG SRC="apcom-logo.gif" ALT="APCOM:" ALIGN=left WIDTH=140 HEIGHT=180 HSPACE=12></TD>

<TH><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica">

<H1>Application of Computers and Operations Research in the Mineral Industry

<HR WIDTH=75% SIZE=6>

</H1></FONT></TH></TR></TABLE>



<!-- Body of page goes here! -->



<H1><P><CENTER>26th APCOM Proceedings</CENTER></H1>

<H3><P><CENTER>Table of Contents</CENTER></H3>

<P>Foreword<BR>

Organizing Committee<BR>

APCOM International Council<BR>

Published Proceedings of Previous APCOM Meetings<BR>



<H4>Section 1.  Human Resource Development</H4>



<P>1.   VR-Mine - A Virtual Reality Underground Simulation System

(Application to Mine Safety and Training) - D.J. McClarnon, 

B. Denby, and D. Schofield<BR>

2.   Computers in the Mineral Industry - Progress in Malaysia -

K. Azizi and A.J. Lynch<BR>

3.   Computer Based Alternatives to Distance Education for Mining

Engineers - A. Unal<BR>

4.   Computer Education in Mining Engineering Course at WASM - T. S.

Golosinski<BR>



<H4>Section 2.  Geostatistics</H4>



<P>5.   Numerical Maximum Likelihood Method for Estimating the Mean

of a Compound Lognormal Distribution - J. Caers and A. Vervoort <BR>

6.   Visualising QTz Curves for the Lognormal Distribution - 

A. Berckmans and M. Armstrong <BR>

7.   Alternative Mixture Model: Application to the Walker Lake

Data Set - R.V. Cuano<BR>

8.   Comparing the Estimates Obtained from Ordinary and Robust

Kriging - J.F. Costa, A.H. White and M.T.M.B. Vilhena<BR>

9.   Fast Multidimensional Interpolations - F.G. Horowitz, 

P. Hornby, D. Bone, and M. Craig <BR>



<H4>Section 3.  Geomechanics Applications I</H4>



<P>10.  Laboratory and In-situ Assessment of Rock Mass Quality -

D.R. Pearce and L. Wade<BR>

11.  Monitoring System for Geomechanic Support of Design and

Mining Operations at Underground Coal Mines - G.I. Gritsko, B.V.

Vlasenko, and V.P. Potapov<BR>

12.  Windows Based Software for Predicting Damage Between 

Multi-Seam Mines - R. Kanniganti, C. Haycocks, and M. Karmis<BR>

13.  Assessment of Potential Domain of Roof Fall in Coal Mine

Entry with Probability-Based Dynamic Programming Approach - F.F.

Peng, V.Z. Sun, and S.S. Peng<BR>



<H4>Section 4.  Geostatistical Application</H4>



<P>14.  Confidence Intervals for Local Estimation: Application to

the Witwatersrand Basin - C. Roth and M. Armstrong<BR>

15.  Geostatistical Reserve Estimation in Dorreh Barite Mine - 

H. Madani and A.M. Mohammadi<BR>

16.  Operational Grade Modelling at the Breitenau Magnesite Mine

- R. Prissang, E. Spyridonos, W. Skala, and T. Frommer <BR>

17.  Application of Cokriging to Integrate Drillhole and

Blasthole Data in Ore Reserve Estimation - A. Arik<BR>



<H4>Section 5.  Geomechanics Applications II</H4>



<P>18.  Numerical-Cognitive Coupling for Integrating Geotechnical

Design with Existing Mine Planning and Design System - A.J. Basu

and J. Corvetti<BR>

19.  Application of Computer Assisted Modeling to Blast Design

and Evaluation in Surface Mines - F. Sames<BR>

20.  Analysis and Visualization of Drilling and Blasting Data

with the Software "Surpac"- P. Moser, I. Oberndorfer, and M.

Siefert<BR>

21.  Concurrent Cutting and Supporting System for Longwall Entry

Development in Australia - A. Misra, N.I. Aziz, and R. Melrose<BR>



<H4>Section 6.  Mining Systems Simulation</H4>



<P>22.  Computer Simulation in the Mineral Industries: Analytical

and International Trends - D.R. Kalasky and J.M. Mutmansky<BR>

23.  Simulation Modelling of Underground Hardrock Mining

Operations Using Wittness - N. Runciman, N. Vagenas, and G. Newson<BR>

24.  Simulation of a Truck-Shovel System Using Arena - E.Y. Baafi

and M. Ataeepour<BR>

25.  Simulation and Animation of the Materials Handling for a

Working Smelter - J.R. Sturgul, K-C. Ritter, and T Fliess<BR>

26.  Prediction of Diamond Wire Cutting Performance by Computer

Simulation - R. Ciccu, G. Massacci, and A. Vargiu<BR>



<H4>Section 7.  Mine Planning - Underground</H4>



<P>27.  Practical Application of Production Planning in Nizna Slana

by Means of Operations Research and Knowledge-Based Techniques -

F.-L. Wilke, J. Fabian, and D. Oravec<BR>

28.  High-Efficiency Assessment and Valuation of Underground

Mining Methods - T. Oberndorfer <BR>

29.  Short-Range Planning: From Scheduling to Sequencing - 

J. Schleifer <BR>

30.  Development of Computer - Aided Underground Mine Planning at

Nkana Division of ZCCM Limited - E.K.C. Chanda and M.S. Kabibwa<BR>

31.  Shapes of Robotization in Mining - V.L. Konyukh<BR>



<H4>Section 8.  In-Situ Flow Process Modelling</H4>



<P>32.  Numerical Analysis of Groundwater Flow in a Bore Hole with a

Cylindrical Obstacle: Basic Relationship for Measurement of

Seepage Flow Velocity - S. Akibayashi, K. Sasaki, 0. Wei, and 

T. Murakami<BR>

33.  Numerical Modeling of Gas Emission Rate from a Longwall Goaf 

in a Thick Coal Seam - A. Saghafi<BR>

34.  Expert System of In-situ Leaching of Uranium - H. Wang, Y.

Weiping, Y. Yu, L. Wan, and D. Zhang<BR>



<H4>Section 9.  Open Pit Mine Planning I</H4>



<P>35.  Pit Optimisation and Mine Production Scheduling - The Way

Ahead - G.S. Thomas<BR>

36.  Lerchs-Grossman Algorithm from a Dual Simplex Viewpoint - R.

Underwood and B. Tolwinski <BR>

37.  Long Range Planning at Chuquicamata Mine - J.P. Camus and

S.G. Jarpa<BR>

38.  Computer Aided Design System for Long Range Planning in Open

Cut Coal Mines - Y.D. Zhang, K.M. Li, R.X. Zhang, S.G. Li, Y.J.

Hou, and S.D. Li<BR>



<H4>Section 10.  Mineral Processing Applications I</H4>



<P>39.  Mineral Liberation: A Population Balance Approach - D.M.

Weedon and T.J. Napier-Munn<BR>

40.  Simulation of Flotation Process - J.B. Rubinstein, S.T.

Hall, and V.I. Badenicov<BR>

41.  Mathematical Statistics, Circuit Simulation and Evolutive

Operativity of the Chalcopyrite Flotation Performance - B.K.

Krstev<BR>

42.  Computationally Efficient Technique for Separation Data

Balancing - A.I.A. Salama<BR>



<H4>Section 11. Open Pit Mine Planning II</H4>



<P>43.  Some Practical Aspects of Open Pit Mine Planning - W-L. Cai

and  A.F. Banfield<BR>

44.  Open Pit Optimization Using Artificial Neural Networks on

Conditionally Simulated Blocks - P.K. Achireko and S. Frimpong<BR>

45.  Applications of Computer-Based 3D-Visualization in Quarry

Planning - M. Honerkamp and C. Mann<BR>

46.  Optimal Control on Ore-Rock Excavation in Surface Mining -

Q.X. Yun, G.Q. Huang, and Z.Y. Gui<BR>



<H4>Section 12.  Mineral Processing Applications II</H4>



<P>47.  Strategy for Adaptive Process Control for a Column Flotation

Unit - C.L. Karr<BR>

48.  Fractal Based Approach in Image Analysis of Rock Fragments -

E. Widzyk-Capehart and D.S. Young<BR>

49.  Use of Machine Learning Techniques for the Extraction of

Process Knowledge from Industrial Flotation Plants - F.S. Gouws,

C. Aldrich, and G.P.J. Schmitz<BR>

50.  Ranking of Optimum Beneficiation Methods Via the Analytical

Hierarchy Process - D. Herzog and S. Bandopadhyay<BR>

51.  Utilization of Artificial Intelligence in a Process Study

Software for Ore Dressing Processes - S-L.  Jamsa-Jounela, P.

Kummarapurugu, and M. Teijonsalo<BR>



<H4>Section 13.  Expert Systems Applications I</H4>



<P>52.  Underground and Open-Cut Coal Scheduling Using Expert

Systems - K. Whitchurch, A.A. Cram, N. Ozawa, and K. Koizumi<BR>

53.  Mine Information System Based on an OMT Model of the Mine

and the Deposits - W. Koune<BR>

54.  Intelligent Active-Dispatch System: From Theory to Practice

- N.I. Fedunec and O.E. Fomicheva<BR>

55.  Expert System for Coal Preparation Plant Design - Y. Kuang,

Y. He, S. Liu, M. Lu, H. Liu, and D. Chang<BR>

56.  Neural Network Approach to Automatic Control of Mining

Ventilation - L.A. Puchkov, I.O. Temkin, and V.K. Mesentsev<BR>



<H4>Section 14.  Expert Systems Applications II</H4>



<P>57.  Development of a Knowledge-Based System for Planning of

Selective Mining in Hard-Rock Surface Mines - H.C.  Mult, F.-L.

Wilke, and R. Vogt<BR>

58.  Information System Of Mining Operations Monitoring in

Russian State Coal Company "Rosugol' - K.N. Trubelskoy, V.I.

Postnikov, A.F. Klebanov, and M.Yu. Khoudine<BR>

59.  Mining Systems Production Planning by Fuzzy Linear Modelling

- S. Vujic, G. Cirovic, and D. Radojevic<BR>

60.  Development and Application of an Expert System in Mining

Engineering in China - L. Zhang, S. Luo, X. Xiaohe, and J. Zhou<BR>



<H4>Section 15.  Ventilation Applications</H4>



<P>61.  Use of the Wnetz 3.1 Ventilation Network Programme Including

the Systematic Consideration of the Natural Ventilating Pressure

in Mine Ventilation - H. Gerhardt and J. Tegtmeier<BR>

62.  Analytical System for Ventilation Simulators with Skyline

Nodal Pressure Method and Practical Estimate System for 

Underground Mine Air-Conditioning - K. Sasaki, H. Miyakoshi, 

and K. Mashiba<BR>

63.  Training System for an Engineer to Control Ventilation by

Closed/Open Condition of Regulators in an Underground Network - 

Y. Tominaga, T. Kato, S. Ono, M. Kato, and T. Tanaka<BR>

64.  Application of Object Oriented Programming for Design of

Underground Mine Environmental Systems - M.K. Singh and D.C.

Panigrahi<BR>

65.  Hierarchical Balanced Models of the Coal Mine Monitoring

Systems - V.D. Ayurov and N.O. Kaledina<BR>



<H4>Section 16.  Mine Ventilation</H4>



<P>66.  Bounding and Guessing a Project's Rates of Return - M.M.

Hajdasinski<BR>

67.  3D Numerical Model of Mine Value Stochastic Processes Using

Dynamic Arbitrage Theory - S. Frimpong and J.M. Whitidg<BR>

68.  Mineral Projects Evaluation with the Aid of Micro-Computer -

W. Wu and H.J. Zhang<BR>

69.  Option Approach to Mining Investment Decisions - X. Tang and 

J. Elbrond<BR>



<H4>Section 17. Economic Optimization</H4>





<P>70.  Using MILP to Optimize Period Fix Costs in Complex Mine

Sequencing and Scheduling Problems - B.M. Winkler<BR>

71.  Fuzzy Evaluation in Mining Equipment Selection - J.

Changsheng<BR>

72.  Study of Coal Price Decision Support System - J. Guoan, L.

Xinghua, and L. Bin<BR>



<H4>Section 18.  Mine Planning - Haulage Systems</H4>



<P>73.  Computer Simulation of Mine-Wide Conveyor Transport - V.L.

Konyukh, V.A. Davidenko, H.H. Becker, and S.P. Koltsov<BR>

74.  Computer Simulation of Vibratory Transport - A. Czubak<BR>

75.  Study of Rational Capacity of Surge Bunker in Mine Haulage

System - X. Wang, Y. Zhang, and D. Zhang<BR>

76.  Automatic Control of Conveyor Belt Movement Under the

Function of Stochastic Load - L.Pevzner, V. Dmitriev, and Y.

Babitchev<BR>



<H4>Section 19.  Environmental Planning</H4>



<P>77.  Application of Computer Modeling to the Environmental

Remediation of the Berkeley Open Pit Copper Mine, Butte, Montana

- D. Sipe, M. Wilczewski, and K. Uhlman<BR>

78.  Use of Multimedia in Decision Support in the Environmental

Disposal of Solid/Liquid Wastes - A.S. Atkins and J.A. Rose<BR>

79.  Use of Commercially Available Software Packages to Form a

Unique Environmental Tool - J.W. Oberholzar and P. Linzer<BR>

80.  Using of GIS-Technology for Long-Term Environmental Planning

in Kuzbass Coal Region -A.A. Bykov, S.G. Pushkin, and E.L.

Schastlivtsev<BR>

81.  Industrial and Ecology-Economy Estimation of the Russian

Coalfields' Reserves - V.A. Kharchenko and V.M. Yeremeev<BR>

82.  Model of Sustainable Development as Effective Means of

Ecologically Friendly Study for New Deposits' Development,

Securing Region Environmental Requirements - V.J. Ovdenko, S.N.

Lazarenko, and E.L. Schastlivtsev<BR>



<H4>Section 20.  Information Systems</H4>



<P>83.  Object Oriented Mining Group Model and Relational Data Base

as Basis for Executive Information System - P. Niskanen<BR>

84.  Some Experiences with Solving Mine Planning Tasks by

Heterogeneous Computer Systems - K. Irmscher and F.-L. Wilke<BR>

85.  Intelligent Data Exchange Based on a Consistent Data Model -

S. Henley, P. Hornby, and K. Smith<BR>

86.  Geological Computer Applications in the Uranium Industry -

D.J. Dyet<BR>

87.  What Can WWW Contribute to Mine Management? - W.L. Power, P.

B. Ketelaar, S.J.D. Cox, S. Nichols, N.J. Archibald, and D.C.

Davies<BR>



<H4>Section 21.  Late Papers</H4>



<P>88.  Rock Properties Improvement and its Simulation by Numerical

Methods - E.V. Kuzmin<BR>

89.  Strategic Management by the Diverse Activities of Mining

Enterprises - M.K. Pashkova and I.V. Pomorova<BR>



<H4>Author Index </H4>

