<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting Short Courses
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I>Short Courses</I></H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<H1>
Application of GIS and Remote Sensing Technologies to the Mining Industry
</H1>
<H2>
February 22-23, 1997
</H2>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Overview</B></FONT><BR>
This course will introduce basic concepts of Geologic Information Systems and Remote Sensing (GIS/RS) and their use in mining. The Internet and accessing and downloading datasets are also discussed. Additionally, the use of GIS/RS to the best advantage in real projects is demonstrated. Attendees are encouraged to bring questions relating to their projects. The first day will cover GIS/RS basics; the initial creation of a GIS database, types of GIS analysis, verification of data accuracy, and the output of final maps. Remote Sensing includes discussion of imaging systems and different image types, images processing  techniques, integration of information into the GIS database, and output products. The second day covers Internet access, case studies of projects, and costs and benefits of using GIS/RS. Real projects will be analyzed to show specific applications of GIS/RS. The course will conclude with a discussion of how to get started using GIS/RS in your organization.

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Content</B></FONT>
<UL>
<LI><B>Introduction to GIS</B>
<LI><B>The GIS Database</B>
<LI><B>Analysis using the GIS Database</B>
<LI><B>Hydrologic and Topographic Surface Analysis</B>
<LI><B>Results of Analysis: Map Production and Reports</B>
<LI><B>Introduction to Remote Sensing</B>
<LI><B>Basics of Remotely Sensed Imagery</B>
<LI><B>Processing and Analysis of Digital Imagery</B>
<LI><B>Integration of Information into a GIS Database</B>
<LI><B>Output Products: Reports, Image or Vector Maps, Hardcopy Prints of Imagery</B>
<LI><B>Introduction to the Internet</B>
<LI><B>On-line Access to Digital Data</B>
<LI><B>Case Studies of Specific Projects</B>
<LI><B>Applying GIS/RS to your Projects</B>
<LI><B>Costs and Benefits of Implementing GIS/RS</B>
<LI><B>How to Get Started in Your Organization</B>
</UL>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Instructors</B></FONT>
The course is instructed by Daniel Elroi, GIS Manager, Knight Piesold LLC, Denver, CO, 303-629-8788, dse@kpco.com, Denver, CO and Lisa Wynn, Sr. GIS Analyst, Knight Piesold LLC, Denver, CO, 303-629-8788, lwynn@kpco.com.   

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Meetings Department</STRONG>.

