<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting Short Courses
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I>Short Courses</I></H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<H1>
Converting Practises
</H1>
<H2>
February 22-23, 1997
</H2>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Overview</B></FONT><BR>
One of the oldest techniques of the non-ferrous pyrometallurgical industry is the Peirce-Smith side-blown converting operation. Although the technology is approaching 100 years old, the converting stage of the smelting operation is still regarded with suspicion, fear and a lack of confidence. Too often the batch nature of the process, when added to the above-mentioned factors, limits the overall smelter output significantly. This course is for operators wishing to raise the unit productivity of the converter operations from both the people and mechanical aspects.

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Content</B></FONT>
<UL>
<LI><B>History and Development of Technology</B>
<LI><B>Basic Chemistry</B>
<LI><B>Operating Practices Including Fluxing and Oxygen Usage</B>
<LI><B>Aisle Operations</B>
<LI><B>Keys to Process Control</B>
<LI><B>Training Techniques</B>
<LI><B>Maintenance</B>
<LI><B>Gas Handling</B>
<LI><B>Refractories</B>
<LI><B>Continuous Converting Options</B>
</UL>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Instructors</B></FONT>
The course presenters are an international team led by Tony Eltringham, BHP Copper, San Manuel, AZ (520-385-3621).

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

<P>If you have specific questions about any items here, please contact <A HREF="mailto:smenet@aol.com">SME</A>. <STRONG>Please be certain to address correspondence to the Meetings Department</STRONG>.

