<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting Short Courses
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I>Short Courses</I></H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<H1>
Gold Exploration and Geology of Brazil
</H1>
<H2>
February, 22-23, 1997
</H2>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Overview</B></FONT><BR>
Brazil is experiencing a dramatic increase in gold exploration activity. The negative aspects of the 1988 constitutional changes were rescinded in August, 1995, reestablishing the ability to have majority ownership by foreign mining investors. This change, combined with new tax laws, has reenergized foreign investment in the mineral industry, again making Brazil one of the most favorable countries in Latin America. Brazilian government geologists and industry explorationists will present: (1) the latest news regarding exploration activity; (2) a synthesis of the geology and metallogeny of Brazil; (3) new studies of gold deposits, style of mineralization, age; (4) exploration and mining costs in various settings (Amazon, etc); (5) environmental regulations and procedures; (6) accessing DNPM's land status and CPRM's geological database Internet programs; (7) suggestions on how to work with garimpeiros and garimpeiro organizations. Participants will receive 1:7,000,000 scale geologic and gold maps, numerous government publications and demonstration diskettes of DNPM and CPRM software for accessing land status and geological databases. This course is for both exploration managers and field geologists.
  
<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Content</B></FONT>
<UL>
<LI><B>Geology and Metallogeny of Brazil
<LI><B>Mineral Potential of the Amazon and its Special Tax Status
<LI><B>Geology of the Tapajos Garimpo in the Amazon
<LI><B>Results of the Rio das Velhas Project in the Quadrilatero Ferrifero
<LI><B>Geology and Mineral Deposits of Bahia
<LI><B>DNPM's Titulos Minerarios Land Status and CPRM's Microsiga Geology Databases
<LI><B>Garimpeiro organizations and how to work with them
<LI><B>Latest News on Privatization of CVRD
<LI><B>Case Histories of Successful Mining Ventures
<LI><B>What Does it Cost to Play the Game in Brazil vs. Other Latin American Countries
</UL>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Instructors</B></FONT>
The course is lead/coordinated by Chuck Thorman, CTGS Intl., Inc., Lakewood, CO (303-988-7498). Instructors include; Giovanni Toniatti, Secretary of Mines and Metallurgy; Miguel Navarrete Fernandez Junior, Director General, DNPM; Carlos Oiti Berbert, President, CPRM; Elmer Prata Salomao, EPS Consultoria Ltd (former Director General of DNPM); Umberto Raimundo Costa, President, Companhia Baiana de Pesquisa mineral (CBPM); Luciano de Freitas Borges, Deputy-Secretary of Mines and Metallurgy and General Director of the National Department of Mines and Metallurgy; Sabino Loguercio, Chief Geologist, CPRM; Stephen Doppler, Balfour Holdings Inc.; plus geologists from  DOCEGEO, CVRD, and private companies working in Brazil.

<P><HR WIDTH=50% ALIGN=left> Please feel free to <A HREF="mailto:pubs@rmii.com">report any problems</A> encountered on this page.</P>

