<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><CENTER><H2><I>
Thursday, February 27
</I></H2>
<H1>
Western Museum of Mining <BR>
and Industry<BR>
&<BR>
United States Air Force Academy
</H1>
</CENTER></FONT>

<TABLE WIDTH=100%><TR><TD><B>
8:00 AM  5:30 PM
</B></TD>	<TD><B>
$60 per person
</B></TD></TR></TABLE>

<H3>Western Museum of Mining and Industry</H3>
<P>A guided tour of the Museum includes presentation of mining artifacts and displays, a social history of the mining West and a demonstration of several steam engines. The Museum collects, restores, and displays mining artifacts for schools and the general public. Unique to this facility is the actual operation of its steam engines, drills, pumps and other mining equipment.</P>

<H3>United States Air Force Academy</H3>
<P>The trip will stop at the Barry Goldwater Air Force Academy Visitor Center. The Center serves as a gateway to the academy, providing information on its history and cadet life. The Center contains exhibits, a theater, restaurant and gift shop. A short movie detailing the academy experience is shown throughout the day. The Cadet Chapel is a one-third mile nature walk from the Visitors Center.</P>
