<H2>
Monday, February 24
</H2>
<H1>
Pikes Peak Country
</H1>
<TABLE WIDTH=100%><TR><TH>8:30 AM  5:30 PM</TH><TH>$60 per person</TH></TR></TABLE>

<P>The Garden of the Gods, Old Colorado City, the Air Force Academy and a spectacular view of Pike's Peak are highlights of this tour along the front range of the Rocky Mountains. The tour will pass Denver Technological Center, Castle Rock and Monument Pass. The first stop will be the United States Air Force Academy and a tour of the beautiful Academy Chapel and Visitors Center. The tour will then drive through the ancient rock outcroppings of the Garden of the Gods and visit the scenic town of Manitou Springs with the majestic 14,000 ft. Pike's Peak in the background. Attendees will have a chance to browse through the shop of this historic district and if time permits the tour will also stop in Old Colorado City.

<P>Tickets are $60 and include bus transportation, guided tour of the Air Force Academy and lunch at Cheyenne Mountain Inn.
