</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I>Companion Tours</I></H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<H2>
Tuesday, February 25
</H2>
<H1>
Dinosaur Tracks
</H1>

<TABLE WIDTH=100%><TR><TH>9:00 AM  3:00 PM</TH><TH>$60 per person</TH></TR></TABLE>

<P>This tour will focus on Colorado's unique rock formations, mountains, mesas, converging rivers and panoramic vistas and visit the Museum of National History. The first stop will be Red Rocks Park, where geological formations rose from the earth more than 12 million years ago. Attendees will see the famous natural amphitheater and the massive rocks that make up this geological wonder. The tour will then visit the preserved outdoor site of an authentic dinosaur track. A guide provides an informative overview of these prehistoric creatures. The final stop will be the Denver Museum of Natural History, featuring "Prehistoric Journey", one of the finest dinosaur exhibits in the country.

<P>Tickets are $60 and include bus transportation, admission to the Denver Museum of Natural History, and lunch at a local restaurant.
