<TITLE>
1997 SME Annual Meeting Technical Program
</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#c0c0c0">

<TABLE WIDTH=100% BGCOLOR="#000000">
<TR><TH>
<IMG SRC="../art/meetlogo.GIF" ALT =" " ALIGN=left>

<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I><BR CLEAR=left>
Underground Mining II-Panel Discussion; Where Do We Go from Here? Does Technology Have Any Great Leaps Left?
</I></FONT><BR>

Tuesday, February 25, 2:00 PM, C112

</H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>Chair:</B>
<DD>D. Arrowsmith, Heritage Mining Co., Ashland, KY
</DL>

<P>New technology doesn't just happen, it begins with a creative thought and is developed by countless hours of researching, experimenting, testing, failing, and trying again. In our attempts to make our current mining practices more efficient, we are missing the opportunity to develop new technology that could revolutionize our industry? Or are we practical, safety-conscious miners who are responding to the current market, in an industry with a finite life? These questions, and more, will be discussed by a panel of well-known professionals from consulting, manufacturing, operations and research. The representatives from each area will begin our discussion by presenting a summary that outlines their perspective on what the industry's needs will be. From this point forward, through panel discussion and questions from the floor, we will analyze the direction that research is taking, review some of the current work being done, and be able to voice our individual opinions as to the brilliance or folly of our current outlook towards the technology of tomorrow. Panelists include:

<UL>
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>T. A. Schwabenbauer</B></FONT>, Joy Mining Machinery, Franklin, PA
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>J. Smith</B></FONT>, Jeffrey Mining Products L.P., Columbus, OH
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>R. L. Grayson</B></FONT>, University of Missouri, Rolla, MO and S. Ray, West Virginia University, Morgantown, WV
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>J. M. Mutmansky</B></FONT>, The Pennsylvania State University, University Park, PA
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>A. B. Sullivan</B></FONT>, Norwest Mine Services, Inc., Washington, PA
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>D. Kostic</B></FONT>, Weir International Mining Consultants, Des Plaines, IL
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>J. W. Murphy</B></FONT>, NIOSH, Pittsburgh, PA
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>W. G. Meister</B></FONT>, Zeigler Coal Holding Co., Fairview Heights, IL
	<LI><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>S. Rowland</B></FONT>, Kerr McGee Coal Corp., Harrisburg, IL
</UL>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Title</B><BR>
<I>Authors</I></FONT><BR>
Description</P>

