<FONT COLOR="#ffffff">
<H1><FONT SIZE=7>
1997 SME Annual Meeting & Exhibit
</FONT></H1>
<FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial">
<H3><I><BR CLEAR=left>
World Overview of Exploration and Mining I - Asia & Africa
</I></FONT><BR>

Tuesday, February 25, 9:00 AM, C102/104/106

</H3></FONT>
</TH></TR></FONT></TABLE>

<DL COMPACT>
<DT><B>Chair:</B>
<DD>D. Silver, Balfour Holdings, Inc., Englewood, CO
</DL>

<P>Understanding the big picture is a complicated task... unless you assemble the world's leading experts into one forum. SME is proud to sponsor its first "Super Session," where internationally-recognized business development professionals share their views and experiences regarding the relationships between changing global geopolitical issues and emerging business opportunities. Come and learn how the dynamics of the world are changing and gain new insights on what the future could hold. These two morning sessions will provide unparalleled perspective and depth on the evolution of the international minerals industry. The longer format will allow for more exhaustive discussions on the factors impacting different regional areas, while also permitting expanded coverage and providing more detailed information about emerging business frontiers. </P>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>North American Markets Financing Global Development: </B><BR>
<I>D. Silver, Balfour Holdings, Inc., Englewood, CO</I></FONT>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Asia/CIS: </B><BR>
<I>R. Kohli, MC Securities Ltd., London, United Kingdom</I></FONT>

<P><FONT FACE="Helvetica,Arial"><B>Africa: </B><BR>
<I>B. Hestor, Denver, CO</I></FONT>

