<p>Welcome to the Advertising Law Resource Center on the World Wide Web. This center 
contains information for advertising professionals. At this site, check out the latest 
advertising law <a href="news.htm">news</a>, <a href="calendar.htm">calendar</a> of important upcoming events, and many <a href="hot.htm">important links to 
government agencies and organizations</a>. If you wish you can receive <a href="order.htm">ordering information 
</a>for <strong>Advertising Compliance Service</strong>. And be sure to check out the <STRONG><a href="order1.htm">Special Offer</STRONG></a> <EM>for Internet visitors only</EM>! (For a more graphical pathway to the world of advertising law information, click <a href="earth.htm">here</a> now!) While this Web Site is designed for current and 
prospective <strong>Advertising Compliance Service</strong> subscribers, it also offers valuable content 
to other advertising professionals as well.</p>
<p>Whether you're an advertiser, an <a href="agency.htm">advertising agency</a>, an advertising or marketing 
professional, or an attorney whose practice includes the <i>surprisingly vast</i> <a href="adlaw.htm">advertising law 
area</a>, there should be content here that's of interest to you. Our latest <a href="dec.htm">news brief</a>, for example, reminds webvertisers what's at stake for those who are unaware of advertising law's many requirements.</p>
<p>Do you prepare or review advertising for an advertiser or advertising agency? You can 
become a &quot;Registered Website User&quot; of <b>The Advertising Law Resource Center</b> by 
sending us e-mail at <a href="mailto:lawpublish@aol.com">lawpublish@aol.com</a>. This will entitle you to a <b>FREE SAMPLE 
ISSUE</b> of <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b>, a <i>$20 value</i>, if you're one of the first 100 
registrants. Be sure to leave your name and mailing address.</p>
