coupons, rebates, premiums, online promotions, coupons, rebates, premiums, online promotions">
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<body>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><p align=center>CALENDAR OF EVENTS</p></h2>

<p align=center><font size=4><strong>NAD WORKSHOP VII: ADVERTISING CREATIVE TECHNIQUES:<BR>
AVOIDING LEGAL HASSLES</strong></font></p>

<P>The Council of Better Business Bureaus, Inc. (CBBB), National Advertising 
Division (NAD) is sponsoring a seminar, "NAD Workshop VII: Advertising 
Creative Techniques: Avoiding Legal Hassles." It will take place on 
December 11, 1996 at Windows on the World, World Trade Center, 
New York City.</P>

<P>This important conference will examine such issues as:</P>

<UL><LI> Puffery: How Far Can You Go?
<LI> Testimonials: In the Eye of the Beholder.
<LI> Demonstrations: A Question of Degree.
<LI> Look and Sound Alikes: Another Question of Degree.</UL>

<P>For more information about this conference, contact Lynne Collins at 
(212) 705-0122 or e-mail at <a href="mailto:collins@panix.com"> collins@panix.com</a>.</P>

<p align=center><font size=4><strong>AAF ANNOUNCES GOVERNMENT AFFAIRS 
CONFERENCE IN 1997</strong></font></p>

<p>The American Advertising Federation (AAF) has announced that its annual 
<b>Government Affairs Conference</b> will take place at the Westin Hotel in Washington, 
DC on March 13, 1997. </p>

<p>If you'd like more information about this important conference, contact AAF at: 
1101 Vermont Avenue, N.W., Suite 500, Washington, DC 20005-6306. Telephone: 
(202) 898-0089. </p>

<p align=center><font size=4><strong>DMA GOVERNMENT AFFAIRS CONFERENCE TO TAKE PLACE<BR>
ON MAY 12-14, 1997</strong></font></p>

<P>The Direct Marketing Association, Inc. (DMA) and Cowles Business Media are 
co-sponsoring the DMA Government Affairs Conference on May 12-14, 1997 at 
the Chicago Marriott Downtown, Chicago, IL. For more information, contact 
DMA at: Telephone: (212) 790-1500; Address: 1120 Avenue of the Americas, New York, NY 10036-6700.</P>
<p align=center><font size=4><strong>PLI FALSE ADVERTISING HANDBOOK AVAILABLE</strong></font></p>

<p>Practising Law Institute (PLI) presented a conference, "False Advertising
and the Law: Coping with Today's Challenges," in New York City on
September 17, 1996. This conference was held at the PLI Conference
Center, 810 Seventh Avenue, New York, NY 10019-5818. </p>

<p>All registrants received a complimentary copy of PLI's
comprehensive <i>False Advertising and the Law: Coping with Today's
Challenges</i> Course Handbook. If you could not attend this conference and 
would like to purchase a copy of this handbook, or would like to purchase 
additional copies, you should call PLI at (800) 260-4PLI or (212) 824-5700, 
or e-mail <a href="mailto:info@pli.edu"> info@pli.edu</a>. </p>

<hr>
<p>For information about subscribing to <B>Advertising Compliance Service</B>, you may contact JLCom Publishing Co., 
L.L.C. by sending your email inquiry to <a href="mailto:lawpublish@aol.com"> 
lawpublish@aol.com</a> <I>or</I> by calling <B>TOLL FREE</B>: 1-888-ADLAW97. You may also use the <a href="order.htm"> order 
form</a> available at this Web Site.</p> 
