<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<p align=center><font size=4><strong>Advertising Agencies</strong></font></p>
<p>If you have any ad review or creation responsibilities, you will benefit from regularly reading the 
articles and news found in <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b>. Did you know, for example, that 
one large advertising agency recently settled Federal Trade Commission charges over that ad 
agency's role in creating certain ads? <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b> subscribers know all 
about it. For a brief online discussion of that FTC case, see the <a href="june.htm"><em>June 1996</em></a> news briefs at this 
Web Site.</p>
<p>For a real eye-opener as to what fate awaits many advertising agencies and other advertisers who 
fail to comply with the Federal Trade Commission's rules, check out this <a href="money.htm">list of costly fines and 
penalties</a> assessed in FTC decisions and in court cases against advertising agencies and 
advertisers as reported in <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b>.</p>
<p>To give you an idea of the scope of coverage in <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b> pertaining to 
advertising agencies, specifically, and advertising legal compliance isssues in general, check out 
our online version of <b>Advertising Compliance Service's</b> <a href="suppleme.htm">Supplementary Index</a>. </p>
