<p align=center><font size=4><strong>TABLE OF ADVERTISING LAW CASES<br>
JANUARY 1996 THROUGH JULY 1996</strong></font></center><br>

<p>The following <b>Table of Advertising Law Cases </b>contains the complete citation of all 
advertising law court cases that have been discussed and/or cited in the permanent 
portion of <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b> for the period, January 1996--July 1996. 
It is broken down by Tab#, Article# and Page#. [NOTE: THE <b>Advertising 
Compliance Service</b> CITATION IS FOUND AT THE END OF EACH COMPLETE CASE CITE.] 
For example, 44 Liquormart, Inc. et al. v. Rhode Island, et al., 18:28.1 can 
be found in <b>Advertising Compliance Service</b> at Tab #18, Article #28, Page 1. </p>

<p>44 Liquormart, Inc. et al. v. Rhode Island, et al., U.S. Supreme Court, Dkt. No. 
94-1140, May 13, 1996, 18:28.1. </p>
<p>American Civil Liberties Union, et al. v. Janet Reno, Attorney General of the 
United States, Civil Action No. 96-963, June 12, 1996, 15:22.1. </p>
<p>American Civil Liberties Union, et al., v. Janet Reno, United States District Court 
for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania, Civil Action No. 96-963, Plaintiffs' 
Memorandum of Law in Support of a Motion for a Temporary Restraining Order 
and Preliminary Injunction, 15:16.3. </p>
<p>American Civil Liberties Union, et al., v. Janet Reno, United States District Court 
for the Eastern District of Pennsylvania, Civil Action No. 96-963, Temporary 
Restraining Order, February 15, 1996, 15:16.3. </p>
<p>American Home Prods. Corp. v. Johnson &amp; Johnson, 436 F.Supp. 785, 792-95 
(S.D.N.Y. 1977), aff'd 577 F.2d 160 (2d Cir. 1978), 1995 U.S. Dist. LEXIS 
16882, *4; 1995-2 Trade Cas. (CCH) P71, 172, 2:268.7; 17:41.2. </p>
<p>American Library Association, Inc., et al. v. United States Dep't of Justice, et al., 
Civil Action No. 96-1458, United States District Court for the Eastern District of 
Pennsylvania, June 12, 1996, 15:22.1. </p>
<p>Avon Prods., Inc. v. S.C. Johnson &amp; Son, Inc., No. 94 Civ. 3958, 1994 U.S. 
Dist. LEXIS 7950, 1994 WL 267836, at *8 (S.D.N.Y. Jun. 15, 1994), 8:71.2. </p>
<p>Blank v. Pollack et al., 95-CV-0392, United States District Court for the 
Northern District of New York, 1996 U.S. Dist. LEXIS 1725, February 9, 1996, 
2:268.3. </p>
<p>Bristol-Myers v. FTC, 185 F.2d 58 (4th Cir. 1950); 24 FTC 1554 (1937), 
4:67.6. </p>
<p>Buckman v. Citicorp, 95 Civ. 0773 (MBM), United States District Court for the 
Southern District of New York, 1996 U.S. Dist. Lexis 891, January 30, 1996, 
12:34.1 </p>
<p>Castrol, Inc. v. Pennzoil Co., 987 F.2d 939, 943-44 (3d Cir. 1993), 2:268.7; 
17:41.2. </p>
<p>Castrol, Inc. v. Quaker State Corp., 977 F.2d 57, 62 (2d Cir. 1992), 2:268.7; 
8:71.2. </p>
<p>Central Hudson Gas &amp; Electric Corp. v. Public Serv. Comm'n, 447 U.S. 557, 
100 S.Ct. 2343, 65 L.Ed.2d 341 (1980), 10:29.1; 18:28.3. </p>
<p>Coca-Cola Company v. Tropicana Prods., Inc., 690 F.2d 312 (2d Cir. 1982), 
2:268.7; 8:71.2; 17:41.2. </p>
<p>Cuisinarts, Inc. v. Robo-Coupe Int'l Corp., 1982 WL 121559 at *2 (S.D.N.Y. 
June 9, 1982), 2:268.7; 17:41.2. </p>
<p>EFS Marketing, Inc. v. Russ Berrie &amp; Company, Inc., et al., Docket Nos. 
94-9119, 94-9157, United States Court of Appeals for the Second Circuit, 1996 
U.S. App. LEXIS 2077, February 12, 1996, 12:34.5. </p>
<p>FTC v. Atida Karr Enterprises, Inc., No. 95-3784 RSWL (Shx) (C.D. Cal. 
October 30, 1995) (complaint filed), 4:69.3. </p>
<p>FTC v. Colgate-Palmolive Co., 380 U.S. 374 (1965), 4:67.6. </p>
<p>FTC v. Dahlberg, Inc., No. 4-94-CV-165 (D. Minn. November 21, 1995) 
(stipulated permanent injunction and $2.75 million in civil penalties), 4:69.5. </p>
<p>Gillette Company, The v. Wilkinson Sword, Inc. and Friedman Benjamin, Inc., 89 
Civ. 3586 (KMW), United States District Court for the Southern District of New 
York, As Corrected, August 18, 1992, 4:68.3. </p>
<p>Glickman v. Wileman Brothers &amp; Elliott, Inc., U.S. Supreme Court, Dkt. No. 
95-1184, 1995 Term, June 3, 1996, 2:275.1. </p>
<p>Gordon and Breach Science Publishers S.A. v. American Institute of Physics, 859 
F.Supp. 1521 (S.D.N.Y. 1994), 8:70.2. </p>
<p>Gordon and Breach Science Publishers S.A., STBS, Ltd., and Harwood 
Academic Publishers GMBH v. American Institute of Physics and American 
Physical Society, 93 Civ. 6656 (LBS), United States District Court for the 
Southern District of New York, 1995 U.S. Dist. LEXIS 16168, November 2, 
1995, 8:70.1. </p>
<p>Greater New Orleans Broadcasting Association, et al., v. U.S. and FCC, No. 
94-30732, United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit, 1995 U.S. App. 
LEXIS 33420, November 30, 1995, 10:29.1. </p>
<p>Herbko International, Inc. v. Gemmy Industries Corp., 95 Civ. 9848 (SHS), 
United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, 1996 U.S. 
Dist. LEXIS 2160, February 26, 1996, 8:71.1. </p>
<p>Hohe v. Casey, 868 F.2d 69, 73 (3d Cir.), cert. denied, 493 U.S. 848 (1989), 
15:22.5. </p>
<p>H.W. Carter &amp; Sons, Inc., and American Marketing Enterprises, Inc. v. The 
