<p>ABOUT THE PUBLISHER </p>
<hr>
<p>John Lichtenberger, Esq. has been the Managing Editor of <a href="about.htm"><b>Advertising 
Compliance Service</b></a>, a prestigious REFERENCE COMPENDIUM devoted to 
the comprehensive coverage of advertising law, since its inception in September 
1981. Mr. Lichtenberger is the chief executive officer of JLCom Publishing Co., 
LLC, which publishes <a href="about.htm"><b>Advertising Compliance Service</b></a>. He is the current 
Publisher and Editor in Chief of <b>ACS</b>. He is the General Editor of the four-volume 
West Publishing Company textbook series, <i>New Jersey Practice: Skills and 
Methods</i>, Volumes 19--21A, which was completed in 1996. He is the author of 
the textbooks, <b>Advertising Compliance Law: Handbook for Marketing 
Professionals</b>, Quorum Books, Greenwood Press, Inc., 1986, and <i>Readings in 
White-Collar Crime</i>, Meckler Publishing, 1991 and the coursebook, 
<i>White-Collar Crime Coursebook '89</i> Meckler Publishing, 1990.</p>
