<P>
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG ALT=InterVU Logo BORDER=0 SRC="../images/intlogosm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+5>
Network Advantages
</FONT></CENTER>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT><IMG SRC="../images/bluebarsm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><BR></P>
<BR>
<UL>
<H4>
<A HREF="#ANCHOR1511516">Increases Video Delivery Speed & Consistency to Viewers</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001201">Increases Site Traffic by Maximizing Simultaneous Accesses</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001301">Improves Interactivity by Off loading Traffic from Web Site</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001401">Higher Quality Videos</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001501">Monthly Activity and Performance Reports</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001551">The Value of Video</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001601">Increases Market Exposure: InterVU Video Guide</A>
<BR><A HREF="#ANCHOR3001701">InterVU Network Service Value - Complete Satisfaction</A>
</H4>
</UL>
<HR>
<UL>
<A NAME="ANCHOR1511516"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Increases Delivery Speed & Consistency to Viewers
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>The InterVU Network uses proprietary technology to improve video delivery performance by seamlessly redirecting Web video file requests to the InterVU Network servers which provides the most efficient delivery route and sustained delivery capability for the requesting viewer. <A HREF="abouts.html#ANCHOR3001400">Performance Comparison</A> is available.</P>
<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001201"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Increases Site Traffic by Maximizing Simultaneous Accesses
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
The InterVU Network allows more simultaneous viewers by distributing video request loads across multiple servers.  The InterVU Network increases robustness by having at least two delivery sources available for the viewer using the InterVU Network Enabled Player.</P>

<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001301"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Improves Interactivity by Off loading Traffic from Web Site
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
The InterVU Network servers contain only the digital video files which accompany a Web presentation.  HTML pages, including text, static graphics, and any back-end databases, all reside on the content providers primary server.  The cost of the primary Web site is reduced because bandwidth and server requirements for distribution of the large digital video files are offloaded to the InterVU Network.</P>
<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001401"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Higher Quality Videos
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
Since video content is placed "electronically closer" to each viewer, Content Providers have more flexibility in balancing between video quality and download time to the viewer.  The InterVU Network provides delivery of higher quality video images in a shorter amount of time.</P>
<BR>
 <A NAME="ANCHOR3001501"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Monthly Activity and Performance Reports
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
Content and network performance is managed, updated and monitored by the InterVU Network Control Center around the clock.  Content Providers utilizing the InterVU Network benefit from InterVU's Internet Performance Database technology and receive documentation on the number of files transferred and the performance of the InterVU Network.
</P>
<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001551"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
The Value of Video
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
Video is a unique medium for communication of large amounts of information in a short period of time.  The television industry features 30 seconds advertisements which are quite effective in promoting anything that has visual appeal. On the Web, messages from CEOs,  music videos, news, sports, advertisements, and product updates all benefit from the heightened impact of video presentation.
</P>
<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001601"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
Increases Market Exposure: InterVU Video Guide
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
Content Providers who participate in the InterVU Network will also have a direct link from the InterVU Video Guide - an online catalog of video pages distributed on the InterVU Network.
</P>
<BR>
<A NAME="ANCHOR3001701"></A>
<FONT SIZE=+2><B><FONT COLOR="#DC143C">
The InterVU Network Value - Complete Satisfaction
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<P>
Content Providers heighten viewer satisfaction by offering higher quality video in a shorter amount of time. They also benefit from lower operating costs and reduced requirements for additional expensive high speed Internet connections.  Video files are offloaded to InterVU Network servers.  These servers provide faster delivery of video segments because they are distributed across the Internet on a variety of Internet Backbones, thus reducing the delays incurred with transmitting files from a single point.
</P>
<P>
The InterVU Network offers usage-based pricing.  Content Providers pay for video messages delivered to viewers, without any additional cost for bandwidth or distribution infrastructure.  The InterVU Network is the <B>low cost, high quality solution</B> for video delivery on the Internet.
<P>
Costs for the Content Provider are further minimized because there is no need to purchase either proprietary video encoding technology (InterVU uses standard MPEG-1) or proprietary video server software.  The only effort required of the Content Provider is to add a flag for each MPEG file with a standard HTML embed tag that indicates the video can be found on the InterVU Network servers.</P>
<P>
Access to the regular page text data at the Web site is less subject to the traffic jams and frustrating delays created by the bandwidth hogs - large video files - which are moved to the InterVU Network servers.
</P>
<P>
The viewer also benefits from the advanced features of the InterVU Player and its special controls which improve the viewing experience.  Features include first-frame preview, video-size adjust, auto-loop, autoplay and family viewing controls.</P>
<P>
There is no expense or inconvenience to the viewer for accessing the InterVU Network.  Viewers just download a free copy of the InterVU Player which is available for Windows 95 and Windows NT for now. Macintosh 68K and PowerPC owners can use the current InterVU Player 0.96 for viewing video from a single site on the InterVU Network.  The viewer also benefits from the many features supported by the Player including cached playback, video-save for hard disk storage, and parental guidance controls for family viewing.
</P>
<P>
In summary, video enhanced Web sites create a more compelling Web offering.  The InterVU Network delivers video quickly and efficiently, which ultimately increases viewer traffic at the Web site.  Customer satisfaction results in more repeat visitors -- which is, of course, the key to future business.</P> 
<BR>
