<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>
InterVU Network Demo
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF", TEXT="#000000", LTEXT="#0000CD", VLINK="#008000", ALINK="#DC143C">
<P>
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG ALT=InterVU Logo SRC="../images/intlogosm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT BORDER=0></A>
<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+5>

Network Demonstration

</FONT></CENTER>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT><IMG SRC="../images/bluebarsm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><BR></P>
<BR>
<UL>
<P>
To see a video using the InterVU Network you'll need to install the InterVU Player and execute the provided SmartVU&#153; Network Optimizer.  This step is critical in selecting the "electronically closest" InterVU Network server required to improve your video network performance.
</P>
</UL>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
<A HREF="../player/player.html">GET <I>InterVU Network Enabled</I> NOW!</A></FONT><BR>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
If you have installed and executed the above program, you can...</FONT><BR>
</FONT>
<FONT SIZE=+2>
<BR>
<A HREF="ivnetdemo.html">NOW RUN THE DEMO</A><BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
