<HEAD>
<TITLE>
InterVU Team
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF", TEXT="#000000", LTEXT="#0000CD", VLINK="#008000", ALINK="#DC143C">
<TABLE ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH=100 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG ALT=Home SRC="../images/hsm.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../help.html"><IMG ALT=Help SRC="../images/hpsm1.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../contact.html"><IMG ALT=Contact SRC="../images/csm.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../copyright.html"><IMG ALT=Copyrt SRC="../images/cpsm.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="../order.html"><IMG ALT=Order SRC="../images/osm.gif" BORDER=0></A></TD> 
</TR>
</TABLE><BR>
<P>
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT=InterVU Logo SRC="../images/intlogosm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+5>
The Management Team
</FONT></CENTER>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT><IMG SRC="../images/bluebarsm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><BR></P>
<UL>
<H4>InterVU's current executive management consists of experienced entrepreneurs and high-technology managers</H4>
<P><B>
Harry E. Gruber - Chief Executive Officer, Founder
</B><BR><BR>
Dr. Gruber is co-inventor of the InterVU Network technology. Dr. Gruber is Chair of the Development Committee for the University of California, San Diego Foundation.  He also serves on an Advisor Council for the University of California, San Diego, School of Engineering.  Dr. Gruber co-founded Gensia, Inc. and was Vice President of Research for ten years.  He was co-founder of Viagene, Inc., Chairman of its Scientific Advisory Board and a member of its Board of Directors.  He provided the founding inventions for both Gensia and Viagene.  Gensia, Inc. and Viagene, Inc., publicly held biotechnology companies, raised in excess of $500 million from investors and corporate partners.   Dr. Gruber has Internal Medicine and Rheumatology Certification from the University of California, San Diego, an M.D. from the University of Pennsylvania, and a B.A. in Biochemistry from the University of Pennsylvania.
</P>
<P><B>
Brian Kenner - Chief Technology Officer, Founder
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Kenner is co-inventor of the InterVU Network technology and is the technical visionary for the Company.  Prior to founding InterVU Inc., Mr. Kenner was Senior Electrical Engineer at Science Applications International Corporation (SAIC), a multi-billion dollar advanced-technology development and research organization.  As Project Engineer, Kenner had responsibility for products ranging from advanced hand-held instrumentation to devices designed to digitize, compress, and transmit both moving and still images over public and proprietary communication networks.  Mr. Kenner holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from the University of California San Diego.
</P>
<P><B>
John Schmuhl - Vice President, Marketing & Business Development
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Schmuhl has more than twenty years of significant experience in video communications, including  major programming and management assignments in both broadcast and cable TV.  Mr. Schmuhl was president of Warner Communications' pioneering QUBE interactive cable venture in the early 80's. This innovative service spawned many of the unique programming formats of the cable era including MTV and Nickelodeon.  More recently, Mr. Schmuhl has held management positions at COMSAT and GTE where he has developed technologies and applications for digital video services.  
</P>
<P><B>
Douglas A. Augustine - Vice President, Corporate Development
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Augustine has a diverse background in creating, capitalizing and operating companies and projects.  Prior to joining InterVU, Mr. Augustine was Chief Operating Officer for the event division of the New York based advertising agency, N.W. Ayer & Partners.  Mr. Augustine was recruited to operate and manage the design, development and operation of the multi-million dollar Olympic facilities created for AT&T ("AT&T's Global Olympic Village") and General Motors ("Century of Motion") for the 1996 Summer Olympic Games in Atlanta.  Mr. Augustine's experience includes Chief Operating Officer of Dennis Conner Sports, President of Arlen Marketing and Director of Development for the America<SUP>3</SUP> Foundation.  In addition to fund raising skills, Mr. Augustine brings extensive relationships with major Fortune 500 companies and the entertainment industry.  Mr. Augustine holds a B.A. degree from the University of California, Berkeley and a J.D. degree from University of San Diego, School of Law. 
</P>
<P><B>
Steve Klein - Director, Business Development
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Klein brings over twelve years of experience from the video, satellite and network communication markets. From July 1994 to May 1996, Mr. Klein served as New Business Development Manager for General Instrument Corporation where he was one of the originating founders of the SURFboard Program - General Instrument's premier Internet Cable Modem Technology and Product Line.   Previously, Mr. Klein held various product management and technical management positions at General Instrument's VideoCipher Division and at Litton Guidance & Control Systems.  Mr. Klein holds an M.B.A. from San Diego State University and a B.S. in Engineering from the Ohio State University.
</P>
<P><B>
Danielle D. McGee, CPA - Director, Finance & Administration
</B><BR><BR>
Ms. McGee has over 20 years experience in finance and accounting for a wide variety of industries.  In addition to "Big 6" public accounting, Ms. McGee has developed systems for emerging "start-ups" and improved infrastructure for established conglomerates.  Prior to joining InterVU, Ms. McGee served as Controller for Viagene, Inc., where she successfully took the company public and subsequently facilitated its acquisition by Chiron Corporation.  From 1988 through 1992, Ms. McGee was Manager of Trust Administration for Service Corporation International, where she had oversight of $300 million in trust assets.  Ms. McGee graduated magna cum laude with honors and distinction from San Diego State University with a Bachelor of Science in Business Administration and is a certified public accountant, licensed in the State of California.
</P>
<P><B>
Peter Czajkowski - Director of Operations
</B><BR><BR>
Prior to joining InterVU Inc. in April 1996, Mr. Czajkowski was the Engineering Manager at Science Applications International Corporation's (SAIC) Military Products Division, where he was responsible for technical, schedule, and budget performance, as well as staff development.  Mr. Czajkowski also held positions as Program Manager and Software Engineer during his 12 years at SAIC.  He previously developed multi-user business applications software for Integrated Decisions Systems, Inc. in Los Angeles.  Mr. Czajkowski holds a B.S. in Economics and Systems Science from the University of California, Los Angeles, and a M.S. in Computer Science from San Diego State University. 
</P>
<P><B>
Arnie Karush - Director, Program Management
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Karush has over 25 years experience in managing software development projects.  He has managed the development of products ranging from shrink-wrapped consumer software, industrial systems and turnkey business systems to on-line software products for mainframes, minicomputers and personal computers.  Prior to joining InterVU, Mr. Karush worked at Intuit, Inc. as Development Director and at ChipSoft as Director of Planning.  He was also a founding member of and served as Vice President of Programs for the San Diego Software Industry Council.  Mr. Karush holds a M.S. in Computer Science from the University of California, Los Angeles, and a B.A. from the University of Pennsylvania. 
</P>
<P><B>
Ken Colby - Director, Research & Development
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Colby as the director of R&D and the creator of a program called Tell-A-Graf,  was the key engineer for Integrated Software Inc's growth from a ten person company to the largest Mainframe graphics company in the world. During his ten year's at Integrated Software, he received a software patent for his work on Layout Intelligence.  Mr. Colby founded Sedona Software, an R&D company which developed software for Symnatec, AccuCobol, Meijer and Metro.  Mr. Colby has a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Purdue University.
</P>
<P><B>
Robert Parker - Director, Systems Engineering
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Parker combines twenty years of hardware, software & systems development experience, including fourteen years in start-up environments, with a very broad experience directing and delivering intuitive software, hardware and system solutions within the digital signal processing, digital telecommunications, and interactive entertainment markets.  Mr. Parker's Bachelor/Master degrees in Mathematics and Physics, are coupled, with three years toward the Ph.D. in Bioengineering, USAF Officers/Pilot training schools, and Project Management School.
</P>
<P><B>
Robert Mudry - Director, Network Technology
</B><BR><BR>
Mr. Mudry has more than 20 years of software development and engineering management experience including expertise in networking, database, real-time software and Internet applications development. Previously, Mr. Mudry was Director of Engineering for CMstat, a Software Engineering Company.  He was a Director of Research and Development from 1984-1992 at Cadence  Design Systems, a Silicon Valley company providing Electronic Design Automation (ECAD) software tools.  Mr. Mudry holds a B.A. degree from the University of California, Santa Barbara.
</P>
</UL>
