<BR>
<P>
<A HREF="../index.html"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT=InterVU Logo SRC="../images/intlogosm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT></A>
<BR><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+5>
Help Wanted
</FONT></CENTER>
<BR CLEAR=LEFT><IMG SRC="../images/bluebarsm.gif" ALIGN=LEFT><BR></P>
<BR>
<H3><CENTER>SPECTACULAR MULTIMEDIA INTERNET OPPORTUNITIES</CENTER>
</H3>
<BR>
<UL>
<H3>Senior Macintosh Programmer</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Innovative Macintosh programmer with experience in development of complex systems using Mac Tool Box.  Build complex system products on top of the Mac OS.  <B>Required -</B> Understanding of  &quot;real-time&quot; applications, pre-emptive and cooperative multi-threading, video and audio multi-media interfaces of the Mac OS, and the TCP/IP protocols.  <B>Desired -</B> Knowledge of MPEG or Quicktime video and audio.</BLOCKQUOTE>


<H3>Windows Programmer</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Develop system and applications software using C++, including codecs for video and audio.  Some products are integrated with Netscape Navigator and/or Microsoft Internet Explorer.  <B>Required -</B> 3+ years C/C++ development in MS-Windows environment.  Familiarity with Windows API.  Understanding of real-time programming issues.  Four year degree.  <B>Desired -</B> Knowledge of MPEG, TCP/IP, WinSock, and MFC.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Database Programmer</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Database schema design and implementation of mid-sized client/server applications in the TCP/IP environment. <B>Required  -</B> 3 to 5 years experience in the design and implementation of mid-sized client/server applications in the TCP/IP environment.  Sybase experience in a SUN/Solaris environment, strong C and SQL skills.  Four year degree.  <B>Desired -</B> Working knowledge of Windows 95/Windows NT, exposure to video and imaging tools, Internet protocols, BSD sockets, database and system administration.</BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Operations Engineer</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>Provide technical support for development and maintenance of InterVU's operational infrastructure, including storage, bandwidth, networking, software, and security for video content and usage accounting.  Support the Director of Operations in maintenance of InterVU Video Network growth plan, including solicitation of service and cost information, and development of hardware and software specifications for servers.  Support the Director of Operations to implement systems and procedures for the distribution, management, and maintenance of customer content on InterVU's video distribution systems.  Activities include hardware and software procurement and installation, at both InterVU and offsite facilities.  <B>Required -</B> Four year degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience. Unix and/or Windows NT system management.  Database programming experience.  C programming experience.  <B>Desired -</B> Perl, HTML, CGI programming experience.  HTTP server administration.  Network management experience.  SQL and other database programming experience.</BLOCKQUOTE>




<H3>Company Information</H3>

<BLOCKQUOTE>InterVU's mission is to become the leader in providing high speed, high quality, cost-effective video delivery services for the Internet.  We are at the leading edge of Internet technology.  If you have the courage to be a pioneer, prefer leading to following, want a chance at the &quot;big win&quot;, and are top rated in your peer group, then please fax your resume to at 619-793-2525, or email to <A HREF="mailto:jobs@intervu.com">jobs@intervu.com</A>.
 We offer competitive benefits, stock participation and Solana Beach, CA ocean
views.</BLOCKQUOTE>
</P>
</UL>
